39:42.214 --> 39:45.217
Shit. Have you tasted
my grandmother’s pork chops?

39:45.300 --> 39:47.219
-(laughs)
-And...

39:47.302 --> 39:49.805
I like white women, too.
Fuck that.

39:49.888 --> 39:52.474
Oh, you’ll see the light
soon enough, Jimmy.

39:52.557 --> 39:54.059
I don’t need to,
hanging around you.

39:54.142 --> 39:56.353
Ain’t you ever heard
of guilt by association?

39:56.436 --> 39:59.481
Well, you already do
have plenty of nice suits.

39:59.564 --> 40:01.566
You given any thought
to switching

40:01.650 --> 40:02.818
from straight to bow ties?

40:02.901 --> 40:04.319
Malcolm, you ain’t never
gonna catch me

40:04.402 --> 40:06.029
dressed up as
one of your soldiers of Allah.

40:06.113 --> 40:07.906
Ah, no.
I-I’ve already seen it, Jimmy.

40:07.989 --> 40:09.616
Th-Those pictures I took of you

40:09.699 --> 40:11.618
-going to practice looking
sharp as a razor. -(Jim laughs)

40:11.701 --> 40:13.161
The spitting image, Cash,

40:13.245 --> 40:16.331
of a-a powerful,
Black Muslim warrior.

40:16.414 --> 40:18.375
-I know it.
-A photo never lies, Jimmy.

40:18.458 --> 40:20.585
Photo never lies.
It-it al...

40:22.129 --> 40:23.130
SAM:
Malcolm?

40:23.213 --> 40:25.006
CASSIUS:
What’s wrong, Malcolm?

40:26.299 --> 40:29.636
Just remembered I left
my new camera in the car.

40:29.719 --> 40:31.555
-Better go get it.
-Now?

40:31.638 --> 40:33.306
Yeah. I just got that camera.

40:33.390 --> 40:34.724
Oh, don’t sweat it, man.

40:34.808 --> 40:36.393
The bodyguards have
this whole place locked down.

40:36.476 --> 40:37.727
They’ll see anybody
messing with your car.

40:37.811 --> 40:39.354
Is everything all right,
Brother Malcolm?

40:39.437 --> 40:41.731
Yes, brother. I just need
to get something from the car.

40:41.815 --> 40:43.692
I’ll accompany you.

40:43.775 --> 40:44.901
Watch the door.

40:44.985 --> 40:46.778
Yes, brother.

40:49.072 --> 40:51.158
Hey, what’s wrong, brother?

40:51.241 --> 40:54.995
Ain’t your shit safe here
in the Black community?

40:55.078 --> 40:56.746
(laughs)

40:56.830 --> 40:59.666
KAREEM: Your friend is
quite the truculent one.

40:59.749 --> 41:01.793
Well, entertaining white people
in the South

41:01.877 --> 41:05.714
will bring the truculence
out of any Black man.

41:05.797 --> 41:07.674
(Cassius grunting, muttering)

41:07.757 --> 41:09.968
♪ ♪

41:10.051 --> 41:12.929
What are you,
a giant fucking baby?

41:13.013 --> 41:15.265
No, man.

41:15.348 --> 41:16.433
I can’t help it.

41:16.516 --> 41:18.059
I’m full of energy.

41:18.143 --> 41:21.563
Well, this party’s
off to a hoppin’ start.

41:21.646 --> 41:22.939
I-I just know we are not
fittin’ to sit here

41:23.023 --> 41:24.482
in this little-ass room
all night.

41:24.566 --> 41:26.401
It’s not like anyone else
is planning a victory party.

41:26.484 --> 41:28.862
The diner downstairs
is open all night.

41:28.945 --> 41:30.447
We could throw
this shindig there

41:30.530 --> 41:32.240
if Malcolm would
lighten the hell up.

41:32.324 --> 41:33.325
CASSIUS: He’s just looking out
for me, Sam.

41:33.408 --> 41:34.784
SAM:
He’s a big boy, Cash.

41:34.868 --> 41:36.578
CASSIUS: Still, you ain’t
got to antagonize him.

41:36.661 --> 41:38.246
He should be able to handle
being called out on his shit,

41:38.330 --> 41:41.708
especially since he’s made
such a name for himself

41:41.791 --> 41:43.126
calling everyone else out
on theirs.

41:43.210 --> 41:44.586
CASSIUS: Why you got
to push back so hard

41:44.669 --> 41:45.962
on everything, Sam?

41:46.046 --> 41:47.422
SAM: ’Cause I’m
a pushy motherfucker.

41:47.505 --> 41:48.715
-And I ain’t changing.
-CASSIUS: Oh, grow up.

41:48.798 --> 41:50.675
Mm... you two.

41:50.759 --> 41:52.344
(silverware clanging)

41:52.427 --> 41:54.846
You want some ice cream?

41:54.930 --> 41:56.806
Everything okay, brother?

41:56.890 --> 41:58.308
Yes, brother.

42:05.065 --> 42:07.150
I should make a call
while I’m down here.

42:07.234 --> 42:09.903
Well, is the phone in your room
not working?

42:09.986 --> 42:13.490
I prefer privacy
when I speak to my wife.

42:13.573 --> 42:15.367
I’d rather not
send all the fellas out.

42:15.450 --> 42:17.035
I’ll be right back.

42:17.118 --> 42:20.330
You know the thing that’ll
make this a little bit better?

42:20.413 --> 42:21.414
CASSIUS:
What?

42:21.498 --> 42:23.583
-Sam’s stash.
-Fuck y’all.

42:23.667 --> 42:25.794
-Come on, man. Where is it?
-No. No way.

42:25.877 --> 42:27.921
Hey, check his guitar case.

42:28.004 --> 42:29.089
For what?

42:29.172 --> 42:30.966
Just look, fool.

42:34.010 --> 42:35.637
Ain’t gonna find it.

42:35.720 --> 42:37.305
I bet he will find something.

42:37.389 --> 42:40.225
I bet you that cheap
purple suit we will.

42:40.308 --> 42:42.143
SAM: Don’t drink
all my shit, neither.

42:42.227 --> 42:44.396
(Cassius exhales)

42:48.316 --> 42:50.026
Yeah.

42:52.320 --> 42:54.239
(sniffs)

42:54.322 --> 42:56.116
Attallah?

42:56.199 --> 42:58.368
ATTALLAH (over phone):
Hi, Daddy.

42:58.451 --> 43:00.704
Hey, sweetheart.

43:00.787 --> 43:02.706
What are you doing up so late?

43:02.789 --> 43:04.541
You woke me up.

43:04.624 --> 43:07.419
-Oh, I’m sorry. I’m sorry.
-(yawns)

43:07.502 --> 43:10.755
I didn’t mean to wake you up,
uh, but I’m glad you answered

43:10.839 --> 43:13.174
because I’ve got
something for you.

43:13.258 --> 43:15.343
You want it now?

43:15.427 --> 43:16.886
Okay.

43:16.970 --> 43:20.682
All right, well, I need you
to get down from the stool.

43:20.765 --> 43:25.061
I want you to take
three big jumps forward.

43:26.938 --> 43:29.149
Now look to your left.

43:29.232 --> 43:31.026
Now what’s in front of you?

43:31.109 --> 43:32.110
ATTALLAH:
Books.

43:32.193 --> 43:33.653
MALCOLM:
Books, that’s right.

43:33.737 --> 43:36.448
Now I want you to take
one of those books.

43:36.531 --> 43:38.616
ATTALLAH:
Which one?

43:38.700 --> 43:40.076
MALCOLM:
It’s your favorite number.

43:40.160 --> 43:44.914
One, two, three,
four, five, six.

43:44.998 --> 43:46.333
MALCOLM:
There you go.

43:46.416 --> 43:48.209
Now open it up.

43:48.293 --> 43:50.754
Take a look inside.

43:53.798 --> 43:55.258
You see it?

43:55.342 --> 43:58.678
-Thank you, Daddy.
-You be a good girl

43:58.762 --> 44:01.598
-and you read that
to your sisters, okay? -Okay.

44:01.681 --> 44:03.058
BETTY: Attallah.
It’s time to go to bed.

44:03.141 --> 44:04.601
ATTALLAH:
It’s Daddy.

44:04.684 --> 44:07.604
I understand, sweetheart,
but it’s time to go to bed.

44:07.687 --> 44:10.231
ATTALLAH: Can I talk to him
for a few more minutes?

44:10.315 --> 44:12.150
-Please?
-(chuckles)

44:13.234 --> 44:14.736
Okay.

44:14.819 --> 44:16.321
(chuckles)

44:16.404 --> 44:18.114
Where are you?

44:23.453 --> 44:25.580
(knock on door)

44:26.915 --> 44:28.666
CASSIUS:
Who is it?

44:29.918 --> 44:32.253
Can I get anything for you,
brothers?

44:33.505 --> 44:35.382
Nah, man.
We’re all good in here.

44:35.465 --> 44:38.718
JAMAAL:
Oh, good. Good.

44:38.802 --> 44:40.095
Good.

44:42.764 --> 44:44.099
Say, champ,
you don’t suppose you could

44:44.182 --> 44:46.851
see your way to signing
an autograph for me?

44:47.852 --> 44:50.355
Uh, yeah, of course, man.

44:50.438 --> 44:52.232
-Yeah, come on in.
-(Jim chuckles)

44:52.315 --> 44:53.608
Yeah. You got to make sure

44:53.691 --> 44:55.568
your superior officer
don’t catch you?

44:55.652 --> 44:58.029
Oh, yeah. Brother Kareem
can run a pretty tight ship,

44:58.113 --> 45:00.573
but he’s committed to teaching
the young brothers discipline.

45:00.657 --> 45:02.909
Yeah, well, I never been a fan
of no tight ship.

45:02.992 --> 45:04.702
Oh, quit messing with
the young brother, Jim.

45:04.786 --> 45:06.538
-Here, give him an autograph.
-JAMAAL: Oh, yeah.

45:06.621 --> 45:07.705
That-That’d be great.
And, actually, champ,

45:07.789 --> 45:09.207
I-I’m a couple
of years older than you.

45:09.290 --> 45:10.291
(chuckles): Oh, see,
I’m such an overachiever,

45:10.375 --> 45:11.668
sometimes I forget.

45:11.751 --> 45:13.503
-(laughs) -JIM: Yeah.
-Now, you know Jim Brown here

45:13.586 --> 45:15.797
is the strongest man
in the whole world?

45:15.880 --> 45:17.715
Oh, yeah.
See, I’m from Toledo.

45:17.799 --> 45:20.468
We’ve been watching Mr. Brown’s
games for years now.

45:20.552 --> 45:21.886
Actually, I almost
got to go to one.

45:21.970 --> 45:24.514
-Oh, yeah?
-Yeah.

45:24.597 --> 45:26.391
-Nah, I didn’t have no money.
-(door closes)

45:26.474 --> 45:27.475
Oh.

45:27.559 --> 45:28.601
Mr. Cooke.

45:28.685 --> 45:31.354
-If you wouldn’t mind.
-(laughs softly)

45:31.438 --> 45:33.690
SAM:
Oh, sure thing, brother.

45:38.069 --> 45:39.279
Hey, man.

45:39.362 --> 45:40.572
Jamaal.

45:40.655 --> 45:42.240
Yeah.

45:42.323 --> 45:43.908
Mind if I ask you a question?

45:43.992 --> 45:45.493
Yeah, sure.

45:46.494 --> 45:48.580
You like being a Muslim?

45:48.663 --> 45:51.791
Well, it... it beats being
a purse thief from Toledo.

45:51.875 --> 45:52.876
(laughs)

45:52.959 --> 45:54.586
Yeah, I know that’s right.

45:54.669 --> 45:56.296
No, I mean, but...

45:56.379 --> 45:59.007
I mean, was it hard,
you know, giving up stuff?

45:59.090 --> 46:01.301
JAMAAL:
Well, I reckon so.

46:01.384 --> 46:04.345
I used to love me a nice
Champale every now and then.

46:04.429 --> 46:06.306
Certainly miss
my grandmama’s pork chops.

46:06.389 --> 46:08.224
-See? -JAMAAL:
And it can be difficult.

46:08.308 --> 46:10.393
-You know, like, the schedule.
-CASSIUS: Yeah.

46:10.477 --> 46:11.644
I mean, but none of that’s

46:11.728 --> 46:13.104
gonna apply to you anyway,
so...

46:13.188 --> 46:14.522
CASSIUS:
What you mean?

46:14.606 --> 46:16.274
JAMAAL:
I’m just saying, I don’t think

46:16.357 --> 46:19.027
you’ll be spending much time
handing out pamphlets is all.

46:19.110 --> 46:20.820
(chuckles): Yeah. Yeah,
I suppose you’re right.

46:20.904 --> 46:22.155
Say, man.

46:22.238 --> 46:24.449
Do you have any regrets?

46:24.532 --> 46:26.659
Oh, regrets? I...

46:26.743 --> 46:28.870
JIM: You know, with hitching
your cart to the Muslim train.

46:28.953 --> 46:30.747
JAMAAL:
Yeah. Uh...

46:30.830 --> 46:32.874
Yeah.

46:32.957 --> 46:35.376
Yes, um...

46:35.460 --> 46:37.170
I th-- I-I think
you can say I do.

46:37.253 --> 46:39.255
Really?

46:39.339 --> 46:42.425
I regret that I didn’t join up
when I was even younger.

46:42.509 --> 46:43.843
-Ah.
-Oh.

46:43.927 --> 46:45.929
JAMAAL: This kid named Rollo
used to chase me home

46:46.012 --> 46:48.056
from school every damn day.

46:48.139 --> 46:49.766
He’s the reason
I stopped going.

46:49.849 --> 46:51.601
-CASSIUS: Oh. -JAMAAL: Now,
I reckon if I would’ve

46:51.684 --> 46:52.936
gotten
with the brothers sooner,

46:53.019 --> 46:54.854
we could’ve nipped it
in the bud

46:54.938 --> 46:57.982
and put a foot in Rollo’s ass.
You know what I’m saying?

46:58.066 --> 46:59.984
Yeah, you don’t need religion
for that, kid.

47:00.068 --> 47:01.528
You could just join a gang.

47:01.611 --> 47:03.696
What’s the damn difference?

47:06.824 --> 47:08.701
Anyway, I-I better get going

47:08.785 --> 47:10.703
before Brother Kareem
gets back.

47:11.829 --> 47:14.207
Hey, we’re all proud
of you, champ.

47:14.290 --> 47:15.583
Aw.

47:17.961 --> 47:20.213
-Thanks, brother.
-Yeah.

47:23.758 --> 47:25.760
(chuckles)

47:25.843 --> 47:27.136
(opens drawer)

47:27.220 --> 47:29.097
(closes drawer)

47:29.180 --> 47:32.350
(unscrews flask)

47:33.309 --> 47:35.436
JIM:
Drink up while you can.

47:37.313 --> 47:39.357
♪ ♪

47:39.440 --> 47:41.651
(grunts)

47:41.734 --> 47:43.361
-Damn.
-Mm-hmm.

47:43.444 --> 47:45.196
-(clears throat)
-(chuckling)

47:45.280 --> 47:47.156
Betty.

47:47.240 --> 47:49.450
BETTY:
Malcolm.

47:49.534 --> 47:50.618
He did it.

47:50.702 --> 47:51.953
I heard.

47:52.036 --> 47:54.455
-(laughing): Praise Allah.
-(laughs)

47:57.542 --> 47:59.460
(inhales)

47:59.544 --> 48:02.338
(crying)

48:02.422 --> 48:04.215
Betty.

48:04.299 --> 48:06.634
-Are you crying?
-(chuckles)

48:06.718 --> 48:09.762
I’m just... happy.

48:10.722 --> 48:12.473
-Oh.
-(car engine starts)

48:12.557 --> 48:13.933
So am I.

48:14.851 --> 48:16.311
So am I.

48:16.394 --> 48:17.854
And is he going to...

48:17.937 --> 48:21.024
He’ll be announcing tomorrow
morning that he’s a Muslim.

48:21.107 --> 48:23.067
(exhales)

48:23.151 --> 48:27.113
Well, do you think
he’ll go along with your plan?

48:27.196 --> 48:32.952
Well, it’s too soon to tell,
but, uh, I feel good about it.

48:34.370 --> 48:37.540
Oh, Malcolm.

48:37.624 --> 48:40.376
You were the only one
who believed in him. (chuckles)

48:40.460 --> 48:44.297
It’s only fitting that you and
Cassius be blessed in this way.

48:44.380 --> 48:46.758
That you do
this thing together.

48:46.841 --> 48:49.510
Well, I really do
believe in him, Betty.

48:49.594 --> 48:51.554
Well, he believes in you, too.

48:51.638 --> 48:53.681
As well as he should.

48:53.765 --> 48:55.516
(chuckles)

48:55.600 --> 48:57.226
Hey, Cash.

48:57.310 --> 48:58.645
Can I tell you something?

48:58.728 --> 49:01.689
Of course, man, anything.

49:01.773 --> 49:03.274
I did a movie.

49:03.358 --> 49:04.734
You produced a movie?

49:04.817 --> 49:07.487
Nah, man, I starred in one.

49:07.570 --> 49:10.323
(chuckles)

49:10.406 --> 49:13.451
Oh, well, that’s great, Jim,
but you’re not an actor.

49:13.534 --> 49:15.286
That’s what I told the cat
who wanted to cast me,

49:15.370 --> 49:17.246
but he put me
in his Western anyway.

49:17.330 --> 49:19.165
-A Western, huh?
-Yeah.

49:19.248 --> 49:22.418
Okay, so, uh,
who-who do you play?

49:22.502 --> 49:24.545
I play a buffalo soldier.

49:24.629 --> 49:26.047
I’m part of this special unit,

49:26.130 --> 49:28.299
and, uh, we’re tracking
this Confederate general.

49:28.383 --> 49:30.343
He’s being protected
by these Apaches.

49:30.426 --> 49:31.469
Damn.

49:31.552 --> 49:33.221
-That sounds pretty good.
-Yeah.

49:33.304 --> 49:35.223
-So you’re the hero?
-One of them.

49:35.306 --> 49:37.392
But my character gets killed
about halfway through,

49:37.475 --> 49:39.268
-so when...
-(laughing)

49:39.352 --> 49:40.561
What?

49:40.645 --> 49:42.313
No, nothing, man. I just...

49:42.397 --> 49:45.149
I should’ve known as soon as
you said "Black action hero,"

49:45.233 --> 49:48.820
the next part of that sentence
was gonna be "who gets killed."

49:48.903 --> 49:50.905
Hmm.

49:50.988 --> 49:52.573
It went well, man.

49:52.657 --> 49:55.076
I think there might be
a future for me in this.

49:55.159 --> 49:57.620
Being the sacrificial Negro
in some Western

49:57.704 --> 49:59.831
ain’t the same as the NFL, man.

49:59.914 --> 50:02.959
But how much you getting paid
to be in this movie?

50:03.042 --> 50:06.504
(chuckles)

50:06.587 --> 50:09.465
$37,000.

50:11.342 --> 50:12.343
-Damn.
-Mm-hmm.

50:12.427 --> 50:13.511
That’s pretty good.

50:13.594 --> 50:15.221
It’s a lot easier
on my knees, too.

50:15.304 --> 50:18.099
Yeah, but the only reason
they want you in that movie

50:18.182 --> 50:20.518
is ’cause people know you
from football.

50:20.601 --> 50:25.231
I mean, you need the game,
just like I need boxing.

50:25.314 --> 50:27.567
We’re all just gladiators,
Cash,

50:27.650 --> 50:29.694
with our ruler
sitting up there in his box,

50:29.777 --> 50:32.697
giving us the thumbs up
or the thumbs down.

50:32.780 --> 50:34.282
Well, I don’t want
no damn ruler.

50:34.365 --> 50:35.867
All right?

50:35.950 --> 50:37.827
Shit, it’s only so much running
one man can do, anyway.

50:37.910 --> 50:39.412
Oh, speak for yourself.

50:39.495 --> 50:44.876
I plan to run, dance and fight
well into my old age.

50:46.335 --> 50:49.714
MALCOLM: Is everything
okay at the house?

50:49.797 --> 50:52.550
The girls behaving themselves?

50:52.633 --> 50:54.093
As best as they can.

50:54.177 --> 50:56.179
(both laugh)

50:56.262 --> 50:58.389
♪ ♪

51:06.314 --> 51:07.648
Malcolm?

51:08.733 --> 51:10.026
Yes?

51:10.109 --> 51:11.444
Is everything okay?

51:11.527 --> 51:13.362
Yes.

51:13.446 --> 51:16.574
Yes, everything’s fine. Uh-huh.

51:18.409 --> 51:19.702
(phone booth door opens)

51:19.786 --> 51:22.121
-Evening.
-Hi, Sam Cooke. (laughs)

51:24.290 --> 51:25.875
SAM:
Hey!

51:25.958 --> 51:28.836
I was wondering what was taking
you so long to find a camera.

51:28.920 --> 51:30.880
I had to check in with Betty.

51:31.881 --> 51:33.966
(imitates whip cracking)

51:34.050 --> 51:36.886
Well, shouldn’t you be checking
in with Barbara at the hotel?

51:36.969 --> 51:39.055
Nah, she’s on her way back
to Los Angeles.

51:39.138 --> 51:42.183
I hope I haven’t unnecessarily
kept you away from her.

51:42.266 --> 51:43.810
No.

51:45.812 --> 51:47.355
What you looking at?

51:47.438 --> 51:49.774
Let’s make our way back
to the hotel, Sam.

52:02.703 --> 52:04.080
Oh, here they come.

52:04.163 --> 52:05.289
My goodness.

52:05.373 --> 52:07.500
You must have super hearing
for real.

52:07.583 --> 52:09.669
I’m Jim motherfucking Brown.

52:09.752 --> 52:10.920
(both laugh)

52:11.003 --> 52:12.505
Hey, uh, remember, man,

52:12.588 --> 52:14.173
just don’t say anything
about the movie shit.

52:14.257 --> 52:15.258
Why are you embarrassed
about it?

52:15.341 --> 52:16.342
It’s not a big deal.

52:16.425 --> 52:18.594
Just don’t say a goddamn thing.

52:18.678 --> 52:20.263
Mum’s the word.

52:22.515 --> 52:23.891
SAM:
Thank you.

52:23.975 --> 52:25.226
Brother Malcolm.

52:25.309 --> 52:27.395
SAM:
What are you handsome, rich...

52:27.478 --> 52:29.355
KAREEM:
Brother Malcolm.

52:30.898 --> 52:32.859
Is there anything
I can help you with?

52:32.942 --> 52:35.069
Uh, no, brother.
We’re-we’re doing just fine.

52:35.152 --> 52:37.864
Well, you know where I am
if you need me.

52:39.407 --> 52:42.118
-God is great.
-MALCOLM: Yes, he is.

52:45.204 --> 52:47.331
♪ ♪

52:51.085 --> 52:52.670
JIM:
What’s with him?

52:52.753 --> 52:54.714
SAM: He thinks
someone’s following him.

52:54.797 --> 52:57.967
You didn’t see those two white
guys across the street, Sam?

52:58.050 --> 52:59.552
I know when I’m being watched.

52:59.635 --> 53:01.137
SAM: How you know
they wasn’t watching me?

53:01.220 --> 53:02.513
Shit, I’m famous.

53:02.597 --> 53:04.557
CASSIUS: They ain’t all
after you, Malcolm.

53:04.640 --> 53:06.058
Yeah, Hoover’s lackeys

53:06.142 --> 53:07.476
have been following me around
so long,

53:07.560 --> 53:09.228
they know where I’m gonna be
before I do.

53:09.312 --> 53:11.022
See what happens when you don’t
get enough exercise?

53:11.105 --> 53:12.940
Your mind goes haywire.

53:17.403 --> 53:18.738
Yeah, as a matter of fact,

53:18.821 --> 53:22.742
maybe some exercise
is just what we all need.

53:24.035 --> 53:25.828
What say we stretch
our legs, boys?

53:25.912 --> 53:28.247
-SAM: Are you serious?
-As a heart attack.

53:33.628 --> 53:36.339
MALCOLM: I know when
I’m being watched, Sam.

53:36.422 --> 53:38.966
Well, your paranoia is really
cramping my style, Malcolm.

53:39.050 --> 53:41.135
Come on, just ’cause
you can’t see bugs don’t mean

53:41.218 --> 53:42.345
they ain’t in the house, Sam.

53:42.428 --> 53:44.221
SAM:
Up on this dirty-ass roof.

53:44.305 --> 53:47.016
Why don’t you be like Bing
Crosby about that shit, man,

53:47.099 --> 53:50.144
and accentuate
the motherfucking positive?

53:50.227 --> 53:51.687
Look at this view.

53:51.771 --> 53:54.482
(sighing)

53:54.565 --> 53:56.734
CASSIUS: I bet
they’re doing them for me.

53:56.817 --> 53:59.904
(all chuckle)

54:00.863 --> 54:02.198
It’s nice, ain’t it, Malcolm?

54:02.281 --> 54:05.159
Yeah, it’s most definitely
soothing, Cash.

54:05.242 --> 54:08.245
The air up here is cooler.

54:08.329 --> 54:11.248
Far away from the prying eyes
of your G-men.

54:11.332 --> 54:13.542
Yeah, well, you joke
all you want, Sam,

54:13.626 --> 54:15.878
but I’m telling you
it’s got worse

54:15.962 --> 54:18.255
since the tension
between me and Mr. Muhammad.

54:19.715 --> 54:21.842
I met with a writer in New York
a few weeks back.

54:21.926 --> 54:24.637
There were two guys following
us through the airport.

54:24.720 --> 54:26.430
Swear it was the same two.

54:26.514 --> 54:29.100
I thought
you didn’t trust writers.

54:29.183 --> 54:30.893
Oh.

54:30.977 --> 54:32.853
This one was a brother, and...

54:32.937 --> 54:35.064
well, this meeting
was important.

54:36.440 --> 54:37.566
I figure I’d better start

54:37.650 --> 54:38.859
getting my life story
documented

54:38.943 --> 54:41.362
in my own words while I can.

54:41.445 --> 54:43.864
What are you talking about,
man?

54:46.242 --> 54:48.077
Jimmy, there’s, uh...

54:49.537 --> 54:52.707
...there’s been this feeling
permeating the air as of late.

54:52.790 --> 54:55.418
-Uh, anger?
-Anxiety?

54:55.501 --> 54:56.919
Humidity.

54:57.003 --> 54:58.254
(chuckles)

54:58.337 --> 55:00.464
MALCOLM:
More like menace.

55:00.548 --> 55:02.299
Foreboding or...

55:03.718 --> 55:05.177
...death.

55:05.261 --> 55:07.471
(fireworks exploding)

55:10.349 --> 55:11.976
Well, Jim’s quitting football

55:12.059 --> 55:14.311
-to become a movie star, y’all.
-Cassius! What the fuck?

55:14.395 --> 55:15.521
Sorry, man. I had to do
something to lighten the mood.

55:15.604 --> 55:16.605
Holy shit, you are?

55:16.689 --> 55:19.275
Oh. Look, hey, hey, man.

55:19.358 --> 55:21.235
I’m not quitting football,
okay?

55:21.318 --> 55:24.280
I’m just exploring other
options for after it ends.

55:24.363 --> 55:25.990
SAM:
I think it’s a great idea.

55:26.073 --> 55:27.992
Yeah, you get
that career going, Jim.

55:28.075 --> 55:30.369
Yeah, well, L.A.’s the land
of milk and honey, baby.

55:30.453 --> 55:32.621
We can do whatever
we want to out there.

55:32.705 --> 55:34.665
You can’t live
in Beverly Hills.

55:34.749 --> 55:36.959
Don’t need to. Got our own
Black Beverly Hills.

55:37.043 --> 55:38.627
And we got the better view.

55:38.711 --> 55:40.296
Baldwin Hills, baby.

55:40.379 --> 55:42.798
Top of the hill,
looks out over the whole city,

55:42.882 --> 55:44.216
mountains in the distance.

55:44.300 --> 55:45.384
Nicer than Harlem.

55:45.468 --> 55:46.802
Hell of a lot nicer
than Overtown.

55:46.886 --> 55:48.596
No tenements or slumlords.

55:48.679 --> 55:52.850
It’s just sunshine,
pools and beaches.

55:52.933 --> 55:54.560
Don’t need no Green Book
telling you

55:54.643 --> 55:56.228
-where you can and can’t go.
-Hmm.

55:56.312 --> 55:59.273
The only color that matters
out in Cali is that green.

55:59.356 --> 56:00.900
You sound like
you might be getting

56:00.983 --> 56:02.777
a bit seduced
out there, brother.

56:02.860 --> 56:04.945
Yeah, you know, I’m the one
doing all the seducing.

56:05.029 --> 56:06.614
Well, you watch out
for this one, Jimmy.

56:06.697 --> 56:08.240
He’ll lead you down
the primrose path.

56:08.324 --> 56:10.576
Shit, the only disasters
out in Hollywood

56:10.659 --> 56:12.620
are up there
on that movie screen.

56:12.703 --> 56:15.206
Now, trust me, Jimmy,
there’s a real future in it.

56:15.289 --> 56:17.708
Well, I should be
in movies, too, then.

56:17.792 --> 56:19.835
Damn, I’m too pretty
not to be up on screen.

56:19.919 --> 56:20.920
SAM:
There you go!

56:21.003 --> 56:22.838
-And you, too, Malcolm.
-Yeah?

56:22.922 --> 56:25.174
-Mm, you could be
our-our director. -(laughs)

56:25.257 --> 56:26.425
Come on, show us the camera.

56:26.509 --> 56:27.760
SAM: Come on, man,
show us the camera.

56:27.843 --> 56:31.055
MALCOLM:
Well...

56:31.138 --> 56:32.681
...it’s a pretty
fantastic camera.

56:32.765 --> 56:33.849
SAM:
All right.

56:33.933 --> 56:35.226
MALCOLM:
Betty got it for me.

56:35.309 --> 56:36.644
-It’s a Rolleiflex...
-Bee sting!

56:36.727 --> 56:38.354
-Oh! -That cam... camera...
-Damn, come on!

56:38.437 --> 56:39.647
-Hey. Hey, guys, over here.
-Sam, please, please. Sam!

56:39.730 --> 56:41.440
-Ha! -MALCOLM: Jimmy,
what, you blew your wig?!

56:41.524 --> 56:43.192
-Give me the damn camera!
-(others laughing)

56:43.275 --> 56:46.112
You lost your mind?

56:47.154 --> 56:48.781
You know how much
this thing costs?

56:48.864 --> 56:51.200
I think we done hit a nerve.

56:51.283 --> 56:53.786
Malcolm done dropped the
affected speech and everything.

56:53.869 --> 56:55.955
Yeah, that’s right.

56:56.038 --> 56:57.706
I got more rep than all three--

56:57.790 --> 56:59.750
one, two, three of you clowns
put together.

56:59.834 --> 57:01.127
Oh, come on, man.

57:01.210 --> 57:04.797
Rep don’t carry over
from decade to decade.

57:04.880 --> 57:06.507
Tired-ass 1940s slang
you using.

57:06.590 --> 57:07.842
JIM: That was definitely
not hep, daddy-o.

57:07.925 --> 57:09.009
SAM:
Talking about "blew your wig."

57:09.093 --> 57:11.137
Just show us the camera, Negro.

57:11.220 --> 57:14.807
Fine, just stop joking
for a second.

57:14.890 --> 57:15.975
Okay.

57:16.058 --> 57:17.184
(laughing)

57:17.268 --> 57:18.477
Jesus.

57:21.147 --> 57:22.982
SAM and JIM:
"You blew your wig."

57:23.065 --> 57:24.233
(Jim laughs)

57:24.316 --> 57:26.068
-"Blew your wig."
-Oh, he’s taking a picture.

57:26.152 --> 57:27.611
Oh, uh, hold on. Wait.

57:27.695 --> 57:30.239
-(chuckling, muttering)
-(clears throat)

57:30.322 --> 57:33.367
-Looking sharp now. -MALCOLM:
It’s a Rolleiflex 3.5.

57:33.450 --> 57:36.620
A German twin-lens
reflex camera.

57:36.704 --> 57:38.581
It’s a fine piece
of engineering, gents.

57:38.664 --> 57:40.958
You see, it has this,
uh, pop-out viewfinder.

57:41.041 --> 57:42.126
Well, it looks bulky.

57:42.209 --> 57:43.502
MALCOLM:
No, Jimmy, it’s a work of art.

57:43.586 --> 57:44.587
JIM:
Hmm.

57:44.670 --> 57:46.422
(camera clicks)

57:47.548 --> 57:49.175
Yeah. Besides, uh, you know,

57:49.258 --> 57:52.052
I’ve always got my Nikon handy
for taking photos on the move.

57:52.136 --> 57:54.847
Like when you’re running
from the Feds?

57:54.930 --> 57:55.931
-(chuckles)
-Yeah.

57:56.015 --> 57:57.892
Or, uh, riding on a camel.

57:58.934 --> 58:01.854
Mm. Where to?

58:01.937 --> 58:04.148
-Mecca.
-(Jim chuckles softly)

58:04.231 --> 58:06.567
Ah, you’re going
to Saudi Arabia?

58:06.650 --> 58:07.943
MALCOLM:
Mm-hmm.

58:08.027 --> 58:09.195
Yes.

58:09.278 --> 58:10.696
All Muslims are
supposed to do it

58:10.779 --> 58:12.489
at least once
in their lives, Sam.

58:12.573 --> 58:15.701
And, well, since I’m not doing
any speaking right now, this...

58:15.784 --> 58:17.828
this feels like
as good a time as any.

58:17.912 --> 58:20.789
Oh, maybe I’ll take a few
detours while I’m out there.

58:20.873 --> 58:22.958
Be quite amazing to see
the Great Pyramids.

58:23.042 --> 58:25.211
Man, that sounds fantastic.

58:25.294 --> 58:26.879
Oh, it will be.

58:26.962 --> 58:29.048
If your schedule permits,
you should join me.

58:29.131 --> 58:31.425
Hey, count me in.

58:31.508 --> 58:32.843
-JIM: Yeah?
-Count me in.

58:32.927 --> 58:35.179
I mean, fine African sisters.

58:35.262 --> 58:37.389
Come on, Jim,
I know you’re down with that.

58:37.473 --> 58:39.725
Oh, with the ladies,
most definitely.

58:39.808 --> 58:40.935
But I’m up for another part.

58:41.018 --> 58:42.353
So, see, in between that
and camp,

58:42.436 --> 58:44.104
I won’t have time
for a trip to Africa.

58:44.188 --> 58:46.732
Hey, you should consider
coming as well, Sam.

58:46.815 --> 58:48.859
Leaving this country
in the rearview for a while

58:48.943 --> 58:51.695
is a great way
to get some perspective.

58:51.779 --> 58:53.656
Nah, I’m busy, too.

58:53.739 --> 58:56.242
One can never be too busy
for some added perspective.

58:56.325 --> 58:58.160
SAM:
Nah, I’m swamped, man.

58:58.244 --> 59:02.289
And I got to prep
to go back to the Copa.

59:02.373 --> 59:03.707
(laughing):
Oh, come on, man.

59:03.791 --> 59:06.001
You need to go on
and forget about the Copa.

59:06.085 --> 59:07.753
It was not that bad.

59:07.836 --> 59:10.089
CASSIUS:
Come on, man.

59:10.172 --> 59:12.174
All right, fine,
maybe it was that bad.

59:12.258 --> 59:13.634
Well, y-you don’t shuck
and jive enough

59:13.717 --> 59:15.302
for those ofay tastes.

59:15.386 --> 59:18.264
I may not dance around a stage
like Jackie or James Brown,

59:18.347 --> 59:20.349
but that’s not what
I’m selling, all right?

59:20.432 --> 59:24.311
I’m selling my voice,
my words, my image...

59:24.395 --> 59:25.562
my-my message.

59:25.646 --> 59:27.398
MALCOLM:
Your message? Hmm.

59:27.481 --> 59:29.191
The problem is, at the Copa,
you have to sell that message

59:29.275 --> 59:30.567
to a bunch of white folks.

59:30.651 --> 59:32.945
That don’t matter.
They got souls, don’t they?

59:33.028 --> 59:34.280
And every living thing
with a soul

59:34.363 --> 59:35.864
can have that soul tapped into.

59:35.948 --> 59:37.241
-I thought you’d know that.
-Do you think,

59:37.324 --> 59:38.701
just maybe,
your energy’s misdirected, Sam,

59:38.784 --> 59:39.910
trying to tap into
white people’s souls?

59:39.994 --> 59:41.745
No, I don’t.

59:41.829 --> 59:43.706
If I win them over,
playing our music,

59:43.789 --> 59:45.708
I’m-I’m knocking down doors
for everybody.

59:45.791 --> 59:47.001
You watch and see.

59:47.084 --> 59:49.795
It’s not gonna always be
the pop charts over here,

59:49.878 --> 59:51.630
Black music charts over there.

59:51.714 --> 59:53.799
-One day, it’s gonna be
one chart... -Mm.

59:53.882 --> 59:55.801
...with one music,
for all people.

59:55.884 --> 59:57.219
What kind of message
are you sending, though,

59:57.303 --> 59:58.887
by doing one show
for white folks

59:58.971 --> 1:00:00.431
and a completely different show
for Black folks, Sam?

1:00:00.514 --> 1:00:02.182
-(scoffs)
-You... N-No, listen to me.

1:00:02.266 --> 1:00:04.018
You’re performing in-in places
where the only Black people

1:00:04.101 --> 1:00:06.020
not onstage are the ones
serving the food.

1:00:06.103 --> 1:00:07.771
Don’t you think I know that?

1:00:07.855 --> 1:00:09.940
Can’t tell you how many times
I wanted to reach out

1:00:10.024 --> 1:00:11.442
and punch somebody,
but you c...

1:00:11.525 --> 1:00:13.235
Then, then, then, then
strike with the weapon

1:00:13.319 --> 1:00:15.404
that you have, man, your voice!

1:00:15.487 --> 1:00:17.281
Black people--
we-we standing up.

1:00:17.364 --> 1:00:19.700
-Mm-hmm.
-We-we speaking out.

1:00:19.783 --> 1:00:24.163
Sam, you have possibly
one of the most effective,

1:00:24.246 --> 1:00:26.957
beautiful outlets of us all.

1:00:27.041 --> 1:00:28.584
Y-You’re not using it
to help the cause, brother.

1:00:28.667 --> 1:00:30.794
The hell I’m not.

1:00:30.878 --> 1:00:33.172
I got the masters to my songs.

1:00:33.255 --> 1:00:34.465
I started a label.

1:00:34.548 --> 1:00:35.883
I’m producing
tons of Black artists.

1:00:35.966 --> 1:00:38.302
Don’t you think my determining

1:00:38.385 --> 1:00:40.179
my creative
and business destiny

1:00:40.262 --> 1:00:42.056
is every bit
as inspiring to people

1:00:42.139 --> 1:00:44.975
as you standing up on a podium
trying to piss them off?

1:00:45.059 --> 1:00:47.227
Oh, wait a minute. I forgot.

1:00:47.311 --> 1:00:49.355
That’s all you do!

1:00:49.438 --> 1:00:50.856
Sam, I do plenty.

1:00:50.939 --> 1:00:53.025
Oh, do you? Let’s see.
You suck at sports.

1:00:53.108 --> 1:00:54.318
Well, I-I was never
much into football.

1:00:54.401 --> 1:00:55.527
SAM:
Can’t sing.

1:00:55.611 --> 1:00:57.738
Damn sure can’t make shit
out of no peanut.

1:00:57.821 --> 1:00:59.281
Is there a point
to this rant, Sam?

1:00:59.365 --> 1:01:01.158
My point is that sometimes
I feel like you’re just like

1:01:01.241 --> 1:01:03.160
all the rest of them people out
there, obsessed with the stars.

1:01:03.243 --> 1:01:04.953
-(laughing)
-Oh, no, no, no, Cash.

1:01:05.037 --> 1:01:06.205
-SAM: You look around.
Look around. -Let him finish.

1:01:06.288 --> 1:01:08.499
SAM:
Which one of us don’t belong?

1:01:08.582 --> 1:01:11.418
-Don’t belong?
-(chuckles): Don’t belong.

1:01:11.502 --> 1:01:13.045
Brother Sam,
the only person here

1:01:13.128 --> 1:01:15.047
white people seem to like--

1:01:15.130 --> 1:01:16.423
that would be you.

1:01:16.507 --> 1:01:18.258
-(laughs) -Hey, y’all need
to cool it now, man.

1:01:18.342 --> 1:01:21.261
You know, you always managed
to just be around for shit,

1:01:21.345 --> 1:01:22.471
haven’t you?

1:01:22.554 --> 1:01:24.181
Maybe your daddy
should’ve beaten you better.

1:01:24.264 --> 1:01:25.974
-Jimmy, I’m gonna kick this
motherfucker’s ass. -Oh, whoa.

1:01:26.058 --> 1:01:27.726
You can let him go. Let him go.

1:01:27.810 --> 1:01:29.061
Everything all right,
Brother Malcolm?

1:01:29.144 --> 1:01:30.646
-SAM: What do you want?
-Hey. Hey.

1:01:30.729 --> 1:01:31.939
-Get your motherfucking hands
off me! -Hey. Hey.

1:01:32.022 --> 1:01:33.732
Oh, I don’t think so.

1:01:33.816 --> 1:01:36.360
Our job here is to protect
the brother minister.

1:01:36.443 --> 1:01:39.154
Listen, Kareem, I don’t need
your protection, brother.

1:01:41.031 --> 1:01:45.869
Well, now that that’s settled,
away you go.

1:01:45.953 --> 1:01:47.663
Negro, I will leave
when I am good...

1:01:47.746 --> 1:01:48.831
You best think long and hard

1:01:48.914 --> 1:01:50.958
’fore you wag that tongue
at me.

1:01:57.548 --> 1:01:58.674
God is great.

1:01:58.757 --> 1:02:00.467
MALCOLM:
Yeah, greater than any of us.

1:02:07.641 --> 1:02:08.851
Ah, yeah.

1:02:08.934 --> 1:02:11.103
♪ ♪

1:02:14.314 --> 1:02:16.316
Your security people
are assholes.

1:02:16.400 --> 1:02:18.277
Yeah, I don’t choose them.

1:02:18.360 --> 1:02:19.570
What’s wrong with you, Sam?

1:02:19.653 --> 1:02:21.280
You’re supposed to be
smooth, man.

1:02:21.363 --> 1:02:24.199
Ain’t easy being smooth with
this sandpaper nigga around.

1:02:25.200 --> 1:02:27.119
(sighs):
Shit.

1:02:41.175 --> 1:02:43.594
(sighs)

1:02:43.677 --> 1:02:45.095
You two done fighting now?

1:02:45.179 --> 1:02:47.014
SAM: I wasn’t trying
to fight nobody.

1:02:47.097 --> 1:02:48.724
That’s Malcolm.

1:02:48.807 --> 1:02:50.851
Always pissed off.

1:02:54.730 --> 1:02:56.482
"Pissed off"?

1:02:58.066 --> 1:02:59.818
You say "pissed off,"
Brother Sam?

1:02:59.902 --> 1:03:01.862
You know, what is
going on around us,

1:03:01.945 --> 1:03:04.615
it should make everyone angry.

1:03:04.698 --> 1:03:07.409
Uh, you know,
you bourgeois Negroes,

1:03:07.493 --> 1:03:09.828
you’re too happy,
uh, with your scraps

1:03:09.912 --> 1:03:13.373
to really understand
what is at stake here.

1:03:13.457 --> 1:03:16.210
What, you-you think
Cash being the world champ

1:03:16.293 --> 1:03:18.921
is gonna protect him
from the devils

1:03:19.004 --> 1:03:21.590
that harassed him from
the first day that he got here?

1:03:21.673 --> 1:03:23.133
Mm, I’d like to see them try.

1:03:23.217 --> 1:03:25.219
-MALCOLM: Huh? And Jimmy.
-JIM: Hmm?

1:03:25.302 --> 1:03:27.387
Jimmy is the best
football player in the world,

1:03:27.471 --> 1:03:29.598
but he is also giving money
to Black-owned businesses.

1:03:29.681 --> 1:03:31.808
What, you-you don’t think
that-that threatens

1:03:31.892 --> 1:03:32.893
a lot of white people?

1:03:32.976 --> 1:03:33.977
Hmm?

1:03:34.061 --> 1:03:35.187
You don’t think the FBI is

1:03:35.270 --> 1:03:36.438
probably starting
to follow him around, too?

1:03:36.522 --> 1:03:37.940
Oh, man, now you’re gonna
fucking jinx me.

1:03:38.023 --> 1:03:39.566
And that is why, Brother Sam,

1:03:39.650 --> 1:03:43.779
this-this movement that
we are in is called a struggle.

1:03:43.862 --> 1:03:46.907
Because we are fighting
for our lives!

1:03:46.990 --> 1:03:48.700
(laughs)

1:03:48.784 --> 1:03:51.203
And what words are we hearing
from you, brother?

1:03:52.996 --> 1:03:55.165
Mm, Mr. Soul.

1:03:58.085 --> 1:04:01.213
(needle drops, record crackles)

1:04:01.296 --> 1:04:06.593
♪ Darling, you send me ♪

1:04:06.677 --> 1:04:09.805
♪ I know you send me ♪

1:04:09.888 --> 1:04:11.306
Or maybe this one.

1:04:11.390 --> 1:04:13.433
-♪ Darling, y... ♪
-(music stops)

1:04:15.811 --> 1:04:18.313
♪ I love you, I love you,
I love you, I love you ♪

1:04:18.397 --> 1:04:21.441
♪ I love you,
I love you, I love you ♪

1:04:21.525 --> 1:04:23.443
-♪ I love you, I love you,
I love you ♪ -(snaps fingers)

1:04:23.527 --> 1:04:25.237
-♪ I love you, I love you,
I love you ♪ -(laughs)

1:04:25.320 --> 1:04:29.491
♪ I love you, I love you ♪

1:04:31.118 --> 1:04:34.037
♪ For sentimental reasons ♪

1:04:34.121 --> 1:04:35.831
(laughs)

1:04:35.914 --> 1:04:38.917
-♪ I hope you do
believe me... ♪ -Oh.

1:04:39.876 --> 1:04:41.670
-Wow, Sam.
-(music stops)

1:04:41.753 --> 1:04:43.338
Your music is deep, brother.

1:04:43.422 --> 1:04:45.215
Hey, man, I love them songs.

1:04:45.299 --> 1:04:46.842
Back-never-facing-the-door,
bean-pie-eating,

1:04:46.925 --> 1:04:48.010
self-righteous motherfucker.

1:04:48.093 --> 1:04:49.428
And, to boot, most of them are

1:04:49.511 --> 1:04:52.598
versions of the church songs
that nurtured you.

1:04:52.681 --> 1:04:54.891
You-you twisted them
and you perverted them

1:04:54.975 --> 1:04:56.893
to feed a-a white crowd.

1:04:56.977 --> 1:04:58.437
SAM:
That is bullshit.

1:04:58.520 --> 1:05:01.440
Most of the artists I work with
are gospel sing--

1:05:01.523 --> 1:05:03.650
And do you have any idea what
I’ve given back to the church?

1:05:03.734 --> 1:05:05.861
Do you know-- h-how many times
do I have to hear that, Jimmy?

1:05:05.944 --> 1:05:07.446
You know, that has got to be
the greatest fault

1:05:07.529 --> 1:05:10.198
of you so-called,
uh, successful Negroes.

1:05:10.282 --> 1:05:12.034
-You’ll do something
detrimental... -Here he goes.

1:05:12.117 --> 1:05:14.244
...to your own people
with the promise that-that,

1:05:14.328 --> 1:05:16.997
after you get rich, then you’re
gonna make it back up to them.

1:05:17.080 --> 1:05:18.749
With-with a handout.

1:05:18.832 --> 1:05:20.542
Or some gesture of patronage.

1:05:20.626 --> 1:05:22.919
-Malcolm, Malcolm, all right.
-No, Jimmy.

1:05:23.003 --> 1:05:25.631
And what you don’t get,
Brother Sam:

1:05:25.714 --> 1:05:27.674
you’ve made it, brother.

1:05:27.758 --> 1:05:30.260
But for all the others,
the majority of people

1:05:30.344 --> 1:05:31.970
who had their own
self-destructive dreams

1:05:32.054 --> 1:05:35.390
and didn’t make it,
what they left behind?

1:05:35.474 --> 1:05:38.810
No, all they left behind
is a legacy of negativity!

1:05:38.894 --> 1:05:40.437
But that’s okay,
’cause they all meant well.

1:05:40.520 --> 1:05:42.522
JIM: Malcolm, will you please
have some damn ice cream?

1:05:42.606 --> 1:05:44.524
You will never be loved
by the people

1:05:44.608 --> 1:05:47.194
you’re trying so hard
to win over.

1:05:47.277 --> 1:05:48.445
Never.

1:05:48.528 --> 1:05:51.990
You’re just a windup toy
in a music box.

1:05:52.074 --> 1:05:53.867
A-A monkey.

1:05:53.950 --> 1:05:55.369
That’s what you are.

1:05:55.452 --> 1:05:58.997
You’re a monkey dancing
for an organ grinder to them.

1:06:02.751 --> 1:06:04.336
(whistles)

1:06:04.419 --> 1:06:06.755
Y’all pulled out the knives.

1:06:06.838 --> 1:06:10.175
And if I get cut,
I’m fittin’ to hurt somebody.

1:06:15.597 --> 1:06:17.724
(sighs)

1:06:24.481 --> 1:06:27.109
MALCOLM: Cassius,
who-who were those English boys

1:06:27.192 --> 1:06:29.403
you-you were hanging out with
a couple days ago?

1:06:29.486 --> 1:06:30.779
CASSIUS:
The Beatles.

1:06:30.862 --> 1:06:32.948
MALCOLM:
Yes, The "Be-a-tles."

1:06:33.031 --> 1:06:35.575
(Malcolm scoffs)

1:06:35.659 --> 1:06:37.619
All that time you spent
on the road, Sam,

1:06:37.703 --> 1:06:41.123
entertaining the children
of bigots,

1:06:41.206 --> 1:06:43.667
and at the end of the day,
white folks would still rather

1:06:43.750 --> 1:06:44.960
import their popular music.

1:06:45.043 --> 1:06:47.170
CASSIUS:
Just hold on one second.

1:06:48.672 --> 1:06:51.758
Now, yeah, The Beatles,
th-they’re funny...

1:06:53.427 --> 1:06:55.929
...but they ain’t no Sam Cooke.

1:06:56.012 --> 1:06:58.181
(chuckles softly)

1:06:58.265 --> 1:07:00.475
They’re-they’re...
they’re more of a fad.

1:07:00.559 --> 1:07:04.604
Yeah, well, if not them,
then-then someone else, Cash.

1:07:04.688 --> 1:07:09.192
The bottom line: this is
too important a time, brother,

1:07:09.276 --> 1:07:11.403
to be wasting a-a brilliant

1:07:11.486 --> 1:07:14.072
and-and creative mind
on pandering.

1:07:14.156 --> 1:07:16.324
And it’s too damn hot in here
to be wearing that blazer.

1:07:16.408 --> 1:07:17.951
So what’s your point?

1:07:18.034 --> 1:07:19.494
My-my point is,

1:07:19.578 --> 1:07:22.914
Brother Sam, that I am just
one voice in this struggle.

1:07:22.998 --> 1:07:24.666
Just one.

1:07:24.750 --> 1:07:26.543
And Cassius, Cassius--
he’s another

1:07:26.626 --> 1:07:30.630
who-who pushes us forward with
his fists and with his words.

1:07:30.714 --> 1:07:34.092
And Jimmy, Jimmy pushes us
forward with his fearlessness

1:07:34.176 --> 1:07:36.928
and-and his relentlessness.

1:07:37.012 --> 1:07:38.430
My point is that you, brother,

1:07:38.513 --> 1:07:41.850
you could be the loudest voice
of us all.

1:07:45.312 --> 1:07:47.272
The Honorable Elijah Muhammad
says that if we...

1:07:47.355 --> 1:07:48.607
No, hold on, hold on.

1:07:48.690 --> 1:07:49.941
Now, I ain’t ask you

1:07:50.025 --> 1:07:51.193
what the Honorable
Elijah Muhammad thought.

1:07:51.276 --> 1:07:53.528
I asked you what you thought.

1:07:53.612 --> 1:07:55.071
There you go with,

1:07:55.155 --> 1:07:56.490
"The Honorable Elijah Muhammad
says this,

1:07:56.573 --> 1:07:59.159
Honorable Elijah Muhammad
says that."

1:07:59.242 --> 1:08:01.244
And when the Honorable
Elijah Muhammad tells you

1:08:01.328 --> 1:08:02.746
to shut the fuck up,

1:08:02.829 --> 1:08:04.873
-you damn sure do that, too.
-No.

1:08:04.956 --> 1:08:06.374
What is going on
between the Nation and me, Sam,

1:08:06.458 --> 1:08:08.210
-is way more complicated.
-But you still obey them.

1:08:08.293 --> 1:08:09.294
When they tell you
to come out here

1:08:09.377 --> 1:08:11.421
and-and recruit Cassius

1:08:11.505 --> 1:08:12.923
to become a member of something
you don’t even seem to believe!

1:08:13.006 --> 1:08:14.341
What are you talking about?
I’m not making-- I’m not--

1:08:14.424 --> 1:08:15.550
I’m not making Cassius
do anything!

1:08:15.634 --> 1:08:17.594
Ca-- He came to me for insight.

1:08:17.677 --> 1:08:19.679
He-he had questions.
(stammers)

1:08:19.763 --> 1:08:22.224
His passion for Islam
comes from a pure place, Sam.

1:08:22.307 --> 1:08:24.768
CASSIUS:
"Passion" is...

1:08:24.851 --> 1:08:25.852
(exhales)

1:08:25.936 --> 1:08:28.104
...kind of a strong word.

1:08:39.658 --> 1:08:41.993
Well, you couldn’t stop talking
about how excited you were

1:08:42.077 --> 1:08:44.621
-to come out with your faith
to the world, Cash. -True.

1:08:44.704 --> 1:08:46.998
True. I was.
I am. It’s just that...

1:08:47.082 --> 1:08:48.792
-What is it? -If we’re being
completely honest and all,

1:08:48.875 --> 1:08:50.794
I guess being a Muslim

1:08:50.877 --> 1:08:55.090
sounded like a much better idea
before tonight.

1:08:59.928 --> 1:09:03.515
How could you have
any second thoughts, Cash? I...

1:09:03.598 --> 1:09:05.475
You’re on top of the world.
I-I don’t understand.

1:09:05.559 --> 1:09:09.104
He didn’t actually think he was
gonna win tonight, Malcolm.

1:09:09.187 --> 1:09:11.439
-Cash?
-Course I knew.

1:09:11.523 --> 1:09:13.441
I’m the best...
(exhales)

1:09:13.525 --> 1:09:14.901
I’m the greatest
there ever will be.

1:09:14.985 --> 1:09:16.570
-I’m-I’m just saying that...
-Easy, Cassius.

1:09:16.653 --> 1:09:18.071
No, I’m good.

1:09:19.114 --> 1:09:21.449
I’m just a little nervous
is all.

1:09:21.533 --> 1:09:23.493
That’s natural, ain’t it?

1:09:27.539 --> 1:09:29.332
Malcolm.

1:09:33.587 --> 1:09:36.631
SAM: It takes a hustler
to see a hustle.

1:09:38.383 --> 1:09:41.261
Say, let me ask you something,
Mr. Know-It-All.

1:09:44.389 --> 1:09:48.685
How is it helpful
for Black people

1:09:48.768 --> 1:09:52.314
to run their businesses
different than everyone else’s?

1:09:52.397 --> 1:09:54.524
Dumber than everyone else’s?

1:09:54.608 --> 1:09:56.109
No.

1:09:56.192 --> 1:09:58.695
No one’s accused you of making
bad business decisions, Sam.

1:09:58.778 --> 1:10:00.196
You might as well have.

1:10:00.280 --> 1:10:02.657
You think I don’t know
about the British Invasion?

1:10:03.658 --> 1:10:06.494
I invested
in the British Invasion.

1:10:08.288 --> 1:10:10.248
I have these protégés.

1:10:10.332 --> 1:10:11.416
Valentinos.

1:10:11.499 --> 1:10:13.418
Five Womack brothers.

1:10:13.501 --> 1:10:17.088
The youngest one, Bobby, wrote
this song, "It’s All Over Now."

1:10:17.172 --> 1:10:18.798
Great tune.

1:10:18.882 --> 1:10:20.800
The band records it.
It’s fantastic.

1:10:20.884 --> 1:10:22.385
All over the R&B charts.

1:10:22.469 --> 1:10:27.140
It even went to number 94
on Billboard’s Hot 100.

1:10:27.223 --> 1:10:29.559
Then I get a call from England.

1:10:29.643 --> 1:10:31.478
One of these British bands
wants to record

1:10:31.561 --> 1:10:33.063
-a cover version.
-The Beatles?

1:10:33.146 --> 1:10:35.148
Nah, Cash. They call themselves
the Rolling Stones.

1:10:35.231 --> 1:10:36.608
Oh, like the Muddy Waters song.

1:10:36.691 --> 1:10:37.984
SAM:
Exactly.

1:10:38.068 --> 1:10:39.653
So, Bobby’s like, you know,
"No damn way, man.

1:10:39.736 --> 1:10:41.029
That’s our song, man."

1:10:41.112 --> 1:10:43.073
But... I get the final say,

1:10:43.156 --> 1:10:44.866
and I’m looking
at the big picture.

1:10:44.950 --> 1:10:47.619
And I give the Rolling Stones
permission to record it.

1:10:47.702 --> 1:10:49.871
-You did?
-I did.

1:10:49.955 --> 1:10:51.331
Mm, mm, mm.

1:10:51.414 --> 1:10:53.667
And the Rolling Stones’ version
of the song

1:10:53.750 --> 1:10:56.336
goes all the way to number one.

1:10:56.419 --> 1:10:58.797
Not on the R&B charts.

1:10:58.880 --> 1:11:00.924
Pop charts.

1:11:01.007 --> 1:11:02.884
But, of course, you know,

1:11:02.968 --> 1:11:04.302
once this version
of the song gets big,

1:11:04.386 --> 1:11:06.471
Bobby’s version
just disappears.

1:11:06.554 --> 1:11:08.723
Right? Falls off
the R&B charts. It’s just gone.

1:11:08.807 --> 1:11:10.767
So, of course, Bobby’s crushed.

1:11:10.850 --> 1:11:12.727
Yes, as well he should be, Sam.

1:11:12.811 --> 1:11:15.397
Let me finish.

1:11:15.480 --> 1:11:18.316
He’s crushed
for about six months.

1:11:18.400 --> 1:11:21.611
Because, six months later,

1:11:21.695 --> 1:11:24.030
that first royalty check
comes in.

1:11:24.114 --> 1:11:25.115
(snaps fingers)

1:11:25.198 --> 1:11:26.700
And because Bobby’s the writer

1:11:26.783 --> 1:11:28.535
and my company owns
the rights to the song,

1:11:28.618 --> 1:11:31.079
-that means every time...
-(snapping fingers)

1:11:31.162 --> 1:11:34.082
some white girl buys
a copy of that single,

1:11:34.165 --> 1:11:36.209
she putting money
into my pockets.

1:11:36.292 --> 1:11:38.086
Our pockets.

1:11:38.169 --> 1:11:39.337
(Malcolm chuckling softly)

1:11:39.421 --> 1:11:40.797
White boys out there
touring around,

1:11:40.880 --> 1:11:42.716
they ain’t even know
they working for us.

1:11:42.799 --> 1:11:43.883
Next thing you know,
Bobby’s like,

1:11:43.967 --> 1:11:45.051
"The Rolling Stones
want to cover

1:11:45.135 --> 1:11:46.594
any more versions of my songs?"

1:11:46.678 --> 1:11:48.513
(chuckles)
You know who gets paid more

1:11:48.596 --> 1:11:49.889
than the writer of a song

1:11:49.973 --> 1:11:52.267
that hits number 94
on the Billboard Hot 100?

1:11:52.350 --> 1:11:55.020
-Hmm? -The writer of a song
that hits number one.

1:11:55.103 --> 1:11:56.438
I already knew that.

1:11:56.521 --> 1:11:58.189
Now Bobby knows it, too.

1:11:58.273 --> 1:11:59.649
Tell me
how it’s not empowerment.

1:11:59.733 --> 1:12:01.151
Everybody talks about
they want a piece of the pie.

1:12:01.234 --> 1:12:02.485
Well, I don’t.

1:12:02.569 --> 1:12:05.905
I want the goddamn recipe.

1:12:07.866 --> 1:12:10.660
I congratulate you
on being so shrewd, brother.

1:12:10.744 --> 1:12:12.620
You just don’t get
how everything’s not

1:12:12.704 --> 1:12:14.581
so black and white
like you make it out to be.

1:12:14.664 --> 1:12:17.250
In your mind, President Kennedy
getting assassinated

1:12:17.333 --> 1:12:18.710
is just another one
of those white devils

1:12:18.793 --> 1:12:19.794
getting what they deserve.

1:12:19.878 --> 1:12:21.421
Well, I liked JFK, man.

1:12:21.504 --> 1:12:23.339
My mama cried when he died.

1:12:23.423 --> 1:12:24.466
Mine did, too.

1:12:24.549 --> 1:12:26.134
How do you think
it made me feel

1:12:26.217 --> 1:12:27.761
to have her see my friend
on TV,

1:12:27.844 --> 1:12:28.970
talking about "good riddance"?

1:12:29.054 --> 1:12:30.555
No. I-I didn’t,
I didn’t say-- No.

1:12:30.638 --> 1:12:32.098
Sam, I didn’t say
"good riddance."

1:12:32.182 --> 1:12:34.100
You said it was "chickens
coming home to roost"!

1:12:34.184 --> 1:12:36.728
Yes, I was trying
to make a point, brother!

1:12:36.811 --> 1:12:38.188
-You were paraphrasing.
-SAM: Tell you something else.

1:12:38.271 --> 1:12:40.857
My whole family lives
on the South Side of Chicago,

1:12:40.940 --> 1:12:42.776
not up in Harlem where you are.

1:12:42.859 --> 1:12:45.361
-The Black Muslims...
-"The Nation of Islam" to you.

1:12:45.445 --> 1:12:48.364
The Nation of Islam
is huge in Chicago.

1:12:48.448 --> 1:12:51.076
I know where
Elijah Muhammad’s house is.

1:12:51.159 --> 1:12:52.744
It’s the biggest one
for miles around.

1:12:52.827 --> 1:12:54.412
Looks like
the mayor’s residence.

1:12:54.496 --> 1:12:55.497
Oh, yeah.
I been there for dinner.

1:12:55.580 --> 1:12:56.581
Oh, you been there for dinner.

1:12:56.664 --> 1:12:59.084
So you see how
he lives like a pharaoh.

1:12:59.167 --> 1:13:01.377
Never says nothing about
the crooked Black alderman

1:13:01.461 --> 1:13:03.755
who’s running numbers,
pushing drugs,

1:13:03.838 --> 1:13:06.049
doing all the things
to hurt the community,

1:13:06.132 --> 1:13:08.760
meanwhile condemning
those white devils.

1:13:08.843 --> 1:13:11.346
Come off it, Malcolm.

1:13:11.429 --> 1:13:14.808
(lighter clicks open)

1:13:19.145 --> 1:13:21.189
(chuckles)

1:13:21.272 --> 1:13:23.733
Oh, I got something
for your ass.

1:13:27.487 --> 1:13:29.823
-SAM: ♪ Dum, da-dum, dum. ♪
-(paper crinkling)

1:13:29.906 --> 1:13:32.450
This is the clue that’s gonna
solve the crime, Officer?

1:13:32.534 --> 1:13:34.994
Oh, you could say that.

1:13:35.078 --> 1:13:38.414
You know, I was thinking about
this song I heard on the radio

1:13:38.498 --> 1:13:40.166
the other day, Sam.

1:13:40.250 --> 1:13:44.003
It’s a song
that made me think of you.

1:13:44.087 --> 1:13:46.714
Turns out it’s pretty popular.

1:13:50.385 --> 1:13:53.096
("Blowin’ in the Wind"
by Bob Dylan playing)

1:13:53.179 --> 1:13:58.226
♪ How many roads
must a man walk down ♪

1:13:58.309 --> 1:14:02.856
♪ Before you call him a man? ♪

1:14:04.065 --> 1:14:08.945
♪ How many seas
must a white dove sail ♪

1:14:09.028 --> 1:14:13.700
♪ Before she sleeps
in the sand? ♪

1:14:13.783 --> 1:14:19.497
♪ Yes, and how many times
must the cannonballs fly ♪

1:14:19.581 --> 1:14:24.085
♪ Before they’re
forever banned? ♪

1:14:25.128 --> 1:14:27.505
♪ The answer, my friend ♪

1:14:27.589 --> 1:14:29.883
♪ Is blowin’ in the wind ♪

1:14:29.966 --> 1:14:32.218
-♪ The answer is ♪
-MALCOLM: Mm.

1:14:32.302 --> 1:14:34.304
-♪ Blowin’ in the wind... ♪
-Mm-mm-mm!

1:14:34.387 --> 1:14:35.597
Ooh!

1:14:35.680 --> 1:14:37.849
-(music stops)
-I just love those lyrics.

1:14:38.850 --> 1:14:41.436
Especially in the beginning.

1:14:42.562 --> 1:14:46.441
"How many roads
must a man walk down

1:14:46.524 --> 1:14:49.068
before you can call him a man?"

1:14:49.152 --> 1:14:50.403
It’s as though he’s asking,

1:14:50.486 --> 1:14:52.322
"How much do the oppressed
have to do

1:14:52.405 --> 1:14:56.534
before they can be recognized
as human beings?"

1:14:56.618 --> 1:14:58.119
That really gets you thinking,
don’t it?

1:14:58.203 --> 1:15:00.038
I already know
"Blowin’ in the Wind," Malcolm.

1:15:00.121 --> 1:15:02.373
I heard it
when it first came out.

1:15:02.457 --> 1:15:03.666
It didn’t make you angry?

1:15:03.750 --> 1:15:05.627
Why would it?

1:15:07.045 --> 1:15:10.006
Isn’t this Bob Dylan fella
a white boy from Minnesota?

1:15:11.090 --> 1:15:12.508
So what?

1:15:12.592 --> 1:15:14.552
So?

1:15:16.179 --> 1:15:19.224
This is a white boy
from Minnesota

1:15:19.307 --> 1:15:22.393
who has nothing to gain
from writing a song

1:15:22.477 --> 1:15:25.521
that speaks more
to the struggles of our people,

1:15:25.605 --> 1:15:26.981
more to the movement,

1:15:27.065 --> 1:15:29.317
than anything
that you have ever penned

1:15:29.400 --> 1:15:31.736
in your life, brother.

1:15:31.819 --> 1:15:34.614
I-I know I’m not the shrewd
businessperson you are,

1:15:34.697 --> 1:15:36.658
my brother, but since you say

1:15:36.741 --> 1:15:39.911
being vocally in the struggle
is bad for business,

1:15:39.994 --> 1:15:42.205
why has this old song
gone higher on the pop charts

1:15:42.288 --> 1:15:43.498
than anything you got out?

1:15:47.752 --> 1:15:50.838
Why has this song gone higher

1:15:50.922 --> 1:15:53.174
(chuckles):
on the pop charts

1:15:53.258 --> 1:15:56.261
than anything you got out?

1:15:56.344 --> 1:15:57.845
Hmm?

1:16:10.483 --> 1:16:12.110
-Nope, nope, nope, nope, nope.
-Sam.

1:16:12.193 --> 1:16:13.486
-JIM: Come on, Sam.
-Sam.

1:16:13.569 --> 1:16:14.821
Come back here, man.

1:16:14.904 --> 1:16:15.905
-Sam!
-Sam!

1:16:15.989 --> 1:16:18.283
JIM:
Goddamn it.

1:16:18.366 --> 1:16:20.451
Good riddance.

1:16:34.882 --> 1:16:36.134
That wasn’t necessary.

1:16:36.217 --> 1:16:38.845
Yes, that absolutely
was necessary, Cash.

1:16:38.928 --> 1:16:40.680
-We’re supposed
to be friends, man! -Yes!

1:16:40.763 --> 1:16:42.890
Well, I am his friend,
and that is why

1:16:42.974 --> 1:16:46.936
I am trying to give him
a wake-up call!

1:16:47.020 --> 1:16:51.190
There is no more room
for anyone--

1:16:51.274 --> 1:16:54.402
not you, not me,
not Jimmy, not Sam--

1:16:54.485 --> 1:16:58.031
no one to be standing
on the fence anymore!

1:16:58.114 --> 1:17:03.077
Our people are literally dying
in the streets every day!

1:17:03.870 --> 1:17:07.415
Black people are dying!

1:17:07.498 --> 1:17:09.625
Every day!

1:17:11.377 --> 1:17:14.547
And a line has got to be drawn
in the sand, Jimmy.

1:17:14.630 --> 1:17:18.009
A line that says, "Either
you stand on this side with us,

1:17:18.092 --> 1:17:20.428
or you stand over on that side
against us," Cash.

1:17:20.511 --> 1:17:22.013
And I-I believe,

1:17:22.096 --> 1:17:24.974
I believe in that brother’s
potential, Jimmy,

1:17:25.058 --> 1:17:26.392
too much!

1:17:26.476 --> 1:17:30.021
Too much to let him stay
over on the other side.

1:17:31.731 --> 1:17:34.567
CASSIUS: I better go get him
before he drives off.

1:17:36.235 --> 1:17:38.654
(breathing sharply)

1:17:38.738 --> 1:17:40.948
(door opens, closes)

1:17:50.750 --> 1:17:52.752
(groans softly)

1:17:53.628 --> 1:17:55.380
(grunts)

1:17:55.463 --> 1:17:57.673
(breathing heavily)

1:18:14.357 --> 1:18:16.734
You know...

1:18:16.818 --> 1:18:19.904
I always find it kind of funny
how you light-skinned cats

1:18:19.987 --> 1:18:23.199
end up being so damn militant.

1:18:25.743 --> 1:18:27.161
-How...
-(chuckles)

1:18:27.245 --> 1:18:29.414
(chuckles)

1:18:30.248 --> 1:18:31.874
What do you mean?

1:18:31.958 --> 1:18:35.545
Well, you are yellow
as the sun.

1:18:35.628 --> 1:18:37.672
When I think
about who the most outspoken,

1:18:37.755 --> 1:18:40.883
consequences-be-damned brothers
out there are,

1:18:40.967 --> 1:18:42.135
it’s always
you light-skinned boys.

1:18:42.218 --> 1:18:44.345
You know, you, W.E.B. Du Bois,

1:18:44.429 --> 1:18:45.638
Adam Clayton Powell...

1:18:45.721 --> 1:18:47.223
Well, I-I...

1:18:47.306 --> 1:18:49.559
I never pay any attention
to complexions, Jimmy,

1:18:49.642 --> 1:18:52.603
because we are all,
we are all Black people.

1:18:52.687 --> 1:18:55.648
Don’t suddenly talk to me
like I’m stupid.

1:18:56.816 --> 1:18:59.402
You know we are all
far from the same.

1:18:59.485 --> 1:19:01.487
When the white folks
ain’t around,

1:19:01.571 --> 1:19:03.614
you see
the-the light-skinned girls

1:19:03.698 --> 1:19:05.199
gather together in one corner,

1:19:05.283 --> 1:19:07.618
all the dark-skinned girls
gather in the other and...

1:19:07.702 --> 1:19:08.786
You know.

1:19:08.870 --> 1:19:09.954
Coming up,

1:19:10.037 --> 1:19:11.497
light-skinned cats
get it harder

1:19:11.581 --> 1:19:12.790
from Black people sometimes

1:19:12.874 --> 1:19:15.209
than they do
from the white people.

1:19:16.919 --> 1:19:19.589
Yeah. What are you
trying to say?

1:19:21.591 --> 1:19:23.801
I just wonder
if all this pushing

1:19:23.885 --> 1:19:26.679
and "hard line" this
and "hard line" that

1:19:26.762 --> 1:19:29.765
is really about trying to prove
something to white people,

1:19:29.849 --> 1:19:31.225
or...

1:19:31.309 --> 1:19:33.060
or, Malcolm,
is it about trying

1:19:33.144 --> 1:19:34.729
to prove something
to Black people?

1:19:34.812 --> 1:19:37.315
(Malcolm chuckles)

1:19:38.983 --> 1:19:41.652
Oh, well, I...

1:19:41.736 --> 1:19:43.946
It’s, uh...

1:19:44.030 --> 1:19:47.325
It’s a very interesting way
of looking at things,

1:19:47.408 --> 1:19:48.659
I suppose.

1:19:50.661 --> 1:19:52.121
Yeah.

1:19:52.205 --> 1:19:54.040
Just something I noticed
is all.

1:19:54.123 --> 1:19:55.875
Mm-hmm.

1:19:55.958 --> 1:19:58.085
I just don’t think
you should begrudge Sam

1:19:58.169 --> 1:19:59.629
for being about his business.

1:19:59.712 --> 1:20:01.297
He’s got to be.

1:20:01.380 --> 1:20:04.258
I mean, if the goal is
for us to be free,

1:20:04.342 --> 1:20:06.552
to really be free...

1:20:06.636 --> 1:20:07.762
And you know it is.

1:20:07.845 --> 1:20:12.225
...then the key
is economic freedom.

1:20:12.308 --> 1:20:15.561
And no one’s more
economically free than Sam.

1:20:15.645 --> 1:20:17.772
Shit, technically,
he’s the only one of us

1:20:17.855 --> 1:20:20.024
not waiting on a paycheck
from a white man.

1:20:20.107 --> 1:20:22.276
Oh, I-I’m not waiting
on no paycheck

1:20:22.360 --> 1:20:25.112
-from no white man, Jimmy.
-You don’t have a job, Negro.

1:20:27.114 --> 1:20:29.200
-(clears throat)
-Well, I...

1:20:29.283 --> 1:20:30.952
Shit. In the literal sense.

1:20:31.035 --> 1:20:32.036
-You-you-- Yeah.
-I know what you--

1:20:32.119 --> 1:20:34.038
Yeah, I-I know, I know.

1:20:34.121 --> 1:20:36.374
I know what you meant.

1:20:37.333 --> 1:20:38.501
Hey, man.

1:20:39.835 --> 1:20:43.256
You know, the one thing
white folks are masters at

1:20:43.339 --> 1:20:45.466
is tapping into our passions
to a point

1:20:45.550 --> 1:20:48.844
that we forget
about the important stuff.

1:20:50.596 --> 1:20:53.849
I thought you loved
being the hero of the NFL.

1:20:56.727 --> 1:20:58.896
A hero, you say?

1:20:58.980 --> 1:21:00.356
Yeah?

1:21:00.439 --> 1:21:03.568
I ain’t no damn hero to them.

1:21:03.651 --> 1:21:04.986
No.

1:21:05.069 --> 1:21:08.614
You see, Malcolm,
some white folks...

1:21:08.698 --> 1:21:10.908
some white folks
just cannot wait

1:21:10.992 --> 1:21:14.954
to pat themselves on the back
for not being cruel to us.

1:21:15.037 --> 1:21:17.331
Like we should be
singing hosannas

1:21:17.415 --> 1:21:20.459
just because they found
the kindness in their hearts

1:21:20.543 --> 1:21:23.421
to almost treat us
like real human beings.

1:21:23.504 --> 1:21:27.216
I mean, do... do you expect
a dog to give you a medal

1:21:27.300 --> 1:21:29.427
for not kicking it that day?

1:21:29.510 --> 1:21:31.137
Hmm?

1:21:31.220 --> 1:21:32.972
I hate
those motherfuckers more

1:21:33.055 --> 1:21:36.017
than the rednecks
who just put it all out there.

1:21:36.100 --> 1:21:37.977
And I’ll be damned
if I ever forget

1:21:38.060 --> 1:21:39.729
what they really think of me.

1:21:39.812 --> 1:21:42.648
Well, I have no doubt
that you won’t, Jimmy.

1:21:42.732 --> 1:21:46.694
And the thing
that I love about Sam...

1:21:47.820 --> 1:21:51.032
...is that
he doesn’t forget, either.

1:21:51.115 --> 1:21:54.619
And he does not deserve
you implying otherwise.

1:21:54.702 --> 1:21:56.871
No, I’m not implying, J--
I’m...

1:21:56.954 --> 1:21:59.665
Jimmy, I am implying
that brothers like Sam

1:21:59.749 --> 1:22:01.500
and you a-and Cassius--

1:22:01.584 --> 1:22:03.711
you all are
our greatest weapons.

1:22:03.794 --> 1:22:06.964
We are not anyone’s weapons,
Malcolm.

1:22:11.218 --> 1:22:13.888
You need to be, Jimmy.

1:22:13.971 --> 1:22:17.892
You need to be
for-for us to win.

1:22:20.311 --> 1:22:22.480
♪ ♪

1:22:25.191 --> 1:22:27.193
(sniffles)

1:22:27.276 --> 1:22:29.153
(grunts softly)

1:22:38.996 --> 1:22:40.206
(Malcolm exhales softly)

1:22:44.335 --> 1:22:45.336
(sniffles)

1:22:45.419 --> 1:22:47.588
Hey, man. Hey, hey.

1:22:48.798 --> 1:22:50.883
Malcolm.

1:22:51.717 --> 1:22:53.511
Brother.

1:22:53.594 --> 1:22:54.679
(exhales)

1:22:54.762 --> 1:22:56.681
-Talk to me.
-(smacks lips)

1:22:56.764 --> 1:22:58.683
Tell me now,

1:22:58.766 --> 1:23:00.643
what is going on?

1:23:00.726 --> 1:23:02.103
(Malcolm inhales, exhales)

1:23:04.605 --> 1:23:06.982
(inhales, exhales)

1:23:11.570 --> 1:23:14.198
Ooh...

1:23:14.281 --> 1:23:15.700
-Ain’t no slug bug.
-(chuckles)

1:23:15.783 --> 1:23:18.119
-I know that mother
be trucking. -Man.

1:23:18.202 --> 1:23:20.538
-(chuckles): Oh.
-(laughs)

1:23:20.621 --> 1:23:22.957
Oh, man, they got bread.
Hold on.

1:23:23.040 --> 1:23:25.126
Y’all got any spare change?

1:23:25.209 --> 1:23:27.128
Uh, sure, kid.
Hang on.

1:23:27.211 --> 1:23:29.380
-How’s it going?
-How’s it going, youngblood?

1:23:29.463 --> 1:23:31.716
-Oh.
-Y’all split that.

1:23:31.799 --> 1:23:33.050
Thank you.

1:23:33.134 --> 1:23:34.969
Hey, congratulations, champ.

1:23:35.052 --> 1:23:36.929
-Hit me up with it.
-You got it, brother.

1:23:37.012 --> 1:23:38.097
"Champ."

1:23:38.180 --> 1:23:40.057
I could get used to that.

1:23:40.141 --> 1:23:41.726
Watch out.

1:23:41.809 --> 1:23:45.354
Malcolm will have ’em calling
you "Champ X" like a damn fool.

1:23:47.398 --> 1:23:48.899
(sighs)

1:23:48.983 --> 1:23:51.068
Malcolm’s had it rough
these past few months.

1:23:51.152 --> 1:23:52.778
Oh, Malcolm’s had it rough?

1:23:52.862 --> 1:23:54.029
He’s getting worn down.

1:23:54.113 --> 1:23:56.490
♪ Jesus ♪

1:23:56.574 --> 1:23:58.367
♪ Wash ♪

1:23:58.451 --> 1:24:02.538
♪ My troubles ♪

1:24:02.621 --> 1:24:05.166
♪ Oh. ♪

1:24:07.793 --> 1:24:09.462
So, Muslim, huh?

1:24:09.545 --> 1:24:11.714
It won’t change my friendship
with you and Jim.

1:24:11.797 --> 1:24:14.216
-You don’t know that.
-The hell I don’t.

1:24:14.300 --> 1:24:16.010
We have to be there
for each other.

1:24:16.093 --> 1:24:17.470
Why?

1:24:17.553 --> 1:24:19.930
Because can’t nobody else
understand

1:24:20.014 --> 1:24:22.016
what it’s like being
one of us except us.

1:24:22.099 --> 1:24:23.601
"One of us"?

1:24:23.684 --> 1:24:25.060
You know.

1:24:25.144 --> 1:24:27.313
Young, Black,

1:24:27.396 --> 1:24:28.606
righteous,

1:24:28.689 --> 1:24:31.442
famous, unapologetic.

1:24:33.778 --> 1:24:35.946
There’s gonna be a target
on your back.

1:24:36.030 --> 1:24:39.116
It was gonna be there anyway.

1:24:39.200 --> 1:24:41.744
This ain’t about civil rights.

1:24:41.827 --> 1:24:44.497
Those activists ain’t do squat
about them four little girls

1:24:44.580 --> 1:24:46.207
that got bombed in Alabama.

1:24:46.290 --> 1:24:47.958
That’s why they’re preaching
to a deaf congregation,

1:24:48.042 --> 1:24:51.921
’cause they ain’t giving Black
people what they really want.

1:24:53.255 --> 1:24:54.924
And what’s that?

1:24:56.675 --> 1:25:00.679
What you have
but take for granted.

1:25:02.556 --> 1:25:03.891
Power.

1:25:07.311 --> 1:25:09.563
Black power.

1:25:11.440 --> 1:25:13.484
I like the sound of that.

1:25:13.567 --> 1:25:16.153
So do I.

1:25:16.237 --> 1:25:18.072
My man.

1:25:18.155 --> 1:25:20.407
So do they.

1:25:22.159 --> 1:25:26.497
Power just means a world where
we’re safe to be ourselves.

1:25:26.580 --> 1:25:27.623
Mm.

1:25:27.706 --> 1:25:30.125
To look like we want.

1:25:30.209 --> 1:25:33.879
To think like we want.

1:25:33.963 --> 1:25:36.924
Without having to answer
to anybody for it.

1:25:37.007 --> 1:25:40.970
And after all we put in, don’t
Black folks deserve that much?

1:25:41.053 --> 1:25:43.222
Mm-hmm.

1:25:44.473 --> 1:25:47.852
We can do whatever
we want now, brother.

1:25:49.061 --> 1:25:50.563
So, tell me.

1:25:50.646 --> 1:25:51.730
Hmm?

1:25:52.773 --> 1:25:55.860
What do you want to do?

1:25:58.654 --> 1:26:00.990
I want a damn party.

1:26:01.073 --> 1:26:03.200
(laughing)

1:26:03.284 --> 1:26:06.328
I mean, don’t you?

1:26:06.412 --> 1:26:07.913
Yeah.

1:26:07.997 --> 1:26:10.624
So let’s go.

1:26:10.708 --> 1:26:11.750
Ooh.

1:26:11.834 --> 1:26:13.127
(engine starts)

1:26:13.210 --> 1:26:14.295
(engine rumbling loudly)

1:26:14.378 --> 1:26:17.631
CASSIUS:
Miami, are you ready?!

1:26:17.715 --> 1:26:19.425
The champ!

1:26:19.508 --> 1:26:22.636
Look now! You’ll never see
something so pretty!

1:26:22.720 --> 1:26:24.889
♪ ♪

1:26:30.352 --> 1:26:32.271
(door opens)

1:26:32.354 --> 1:26:35.441
Hey, hey, the gang’s all here.

1:26:35.524 --> 1:26:37.526
-(door closes)
-Good. You caught him.

1:26:37.610 --> 1:26:39.194
SAM:
I wasn’t running nowhere.

1:26:39.278 --> 1:26:42.031
I am ready to take care
of, uh, hosting duties, though.

1:26:42.114 --> 1:26:44.867
-Really? -Malcolm, you’ve had
the floor long enough.

1:26:44.950 --> 1:26:47.870
It’s time to take this party
to the Fontainebleau. (whoops)

1:26:47.953 --> 1:26:50.915
♪ We’re having a party. ♪

1:26:50.998 --> 1:26:52.374
(Cassius hums)

1:26:52.458 --> 1:26:53.500
You’ve obviously forgotten

1:26:53.584 --> 1:26:55.210
Brother Cassius
no longer drinks.

1:26:55.294 --> 1:26:56.837
And you obviously haven’t
smelled his breath

1:26:56.921 --> 1:26:58.130
in the last hour.

1:27:00.382 --> 1:27:02.176
Hey, let it go, man.

1:27:02.259 --> 1:27:03.969
-Let it go.
-(clears throat)

1:27:05.137 --> 1:27:06.513
Malcolm.

1:27:06.597 --> 1:27:07.806
SAM:
Okay.

1:27:09.266 --> 1:27:10.935
All right.

1:27:11.018 --> 1:27:14.188
Sam, what is this, uh,
this problem between us, Sam?

1:27:14.271 --> 1:27:16.315
I don’t got no problem
with you.

1:27:16.398 --> 1:27:18.233
I got a problem with this guy.

1:27:19.985 --> 1:27:22.988
You used to be, you used to be
such a fun cat.

1:27:23.072 --> 1:27:25.532
Now you acting in private
the way you are on camera.

1:27:25.616 --> 1:27:27.952
Sam, I-I...

1:27:28.035 --> 1:27:29.662
was always this person.

1:27:29.745 --> 1:27:33.582
Maybe, but you were also
always so much...

1:27:36.251 --> 1:27:37.544
...more.

1:27:41.340 --> 1:27:42.675
Fellas, y’all ready?

1:27:50.265 --> 1:27:53.352
You remember, uh,
the first time we met, Sam?

1:27:53.435 --> 1:27:55.020
I’m tired of answering
your questions, man.

1:27:55.104 --> 1:27:56.647
Is that a no?

1:27:57.481 --> 1:27:58.482
(sighs)

1:27:58.565 --> 1:27:59.984
Of course I do.

1:28:00.067 --> 1:28:03.320
It was, uh... Harlem.

1:28:03.404 --> 1:28:05.572
You didn’t even know who I was.

1:28:05.656 --> 1:28:06.865
Uh-huh.

1:28:06.949 --> 1:28:09.868
I said that at the time,
but I knew who you were.

1:28:09.952 --> 1:28:12.162
A lot of the brothers
had been requesting shifts

1:28:12.246 --> 1:28:13.956
-outside the Apollo that week.
-Is that a fact?

1:28:14.039 --> 1:28:15.416
That’s a fact.

1:28:15.499 --> 1:28:16.750
And I understood

1:28:16.834 --> 1:28:19.545
because I caught
one of your shows in Chicago.

1:28:20.629 --> 1:28:22.423
You’ve been to one of my shows?

1:28:22.506 --> 1:28:26.093
No. I’ve, uh, been to...

1:28:28.345 --> 1:28:30.347
...five of them.

1:28:31.515 --> 1:28:33.100
Including the one in Boston.

1:28:33.183 --> 1:28:36.437
(chuckles):
Shit. Boston?

1:28:36.520 --> 1:28:37.521
Really?

1:28:37.604 --> 1:28:39.565
Mm-hmm. Really.

1:28:39.648 --> 1:28:41.358
(laughing)

1:28:41.442 --> 1:28:43.193
Well, hell, what happened
in Boston?

1:28:43.277 --> 1:28:45.821
You mind if I recount
the story, Sam?

1:28:45.904 --> 1:28:46.905
No, no. Go ahead.

1:28:46.989 --> 1:28:47.990
-MALCOLM: Yeah?
-Yeah.

1:28:48.073 --> 1:28:50.075
-(cheering and applause)
-Well, uh,

1:28:50.159 --> 1:28:52.661
this show, um, Sam, he was
playing with Jackie Wilson...

1:28:52.745 --> 1:28:55.164
♪ You’ve been gone away ♪

1:28:55.247 --> 1:28:56.457
♪ You know my heart... ♪

1:28:56.540 --> 1:28:57.708
I was there to see Sam,
of course,

1:28:57.791 --> 1:28:59.752
but Jackie was the opener.

1:28:59.835 --> 1:29:01.503
He was doing
his usual routine,

1:29:01.587 --> 1:29:04.214
shuckin’ and jivin’
like those types do.

1:29:04.298 --> 1:29:06.341
♪ Lonely teardrops ♪

1:29:06.425 --> 1:29:07.593
Not really my cup of tea,
you know.

1:29:07.676 --> 1:29:11.013
♪ My pillows never dry of ♪

1:29:11.096 --> 1:29:14.141
♪ Lonely teardrops... ♪

1:29:14.224 --> 1:29:15.893
But thankfully,
it came to an end,

1:29:15.976 --> 1:29:19.480
and, you know, Sam was
getting ready to come onstage.

1:29:19.563 --> 1:29:21.607
-(holding high note)
-(cheering)

1:29:21.690 --> 1:29:22.816
Yeah, I knew he was

1:29:22.900 --> 1:29:25.360
about to class this joint up.

1:29:26.487 --> 1:29:29.073
Yeah! Hey!

1:29:29.156 --> 1:29:31.366
(cheering
and applause continue)

1:29:34.620 --> 1:29:36.497
I warmed them up for you,
brother.

1:29:37.581 --> 1:29:39.249
Don’t fuck up now.

1:29:39.333 --> 1:29:40.793
-(scoffs)
-(pats chest)

1:29:40.876 --> 1:29:45.589
Ladies and gentlemen,
let’s give it up for Sam Cooke!

1:29:45.672 --> 1:29:49.051
MALCOLM: Sam comes, uh,
strolling out onto the stage.

1:29:49.134 --> 1:29:50.135
Cash, the crowd--

1:29:50.219 --> 1:29:51.887
Boom. Wow.

1:29:51.970 --> 1:29:53.972
Ah! Boston!

1:29:54.056 --> 1:29:55.599
(cheering)

1:29:55.682 --> 1:29:57.601
Thank you.

1:29:57.684 --> 1:29:59.019
WOMAN:
Sam, I love you!

1:29:59.103 --> 1:30:00.771
MALCOLM: Sam steps up
to the microphone,

1:30:00.854 --> 1:30:02.606
wraps his hand around it--
you know how Sam does,

1:30:02.689 --> 1:30:04.775
like, uh, he caresses it,
like, uh,

1:30:04.858 --> 1:30:07.152
one might caress
a delicate piece of crystal.

1:30:07.236 --> 1:30:09.446
-(chuckles)
-Or a pretty little fox.

1:30:09.530 --> 1:30:11.323
An NFL championship trophy.

1:30:11.406 --> 1:30:13.617
-You want me to finish this
story, Jimmy? -Oh, go ahead.

1:30:13.700 --> 1:30:16.703
Yeah. Like I was saying,
he-he... he caresses the mic,

1:30:16.787 --> 1:30:19.248
pulls it close to his lips,
opens his mouth...

1:30:19.331 --> 1:30:21.834
-♪ Darling, you... ♪
-(feedback squealing)

1:30:21.917 --> 1:30:23.377
Sound went out.

1:30:23.460 --> 1:30:24.628
-What?
-Mm-hmm.

1:30:24.711 --> 1:30:26.630
(audience murmuring)

1:30:26.713 --> 1:30:28.841
-That wasn’t the sound system,
was it? -(audience booing)

1:30:34.054 --> 1:30:35.973
The microphone is off!

1:30:39.059 --> 1:30:41.395
MALCOLM: I know. H-How’s that
for some bad luck?

1:30:41.478 --> 1:30:43.313
Bad luck, my ass.

1:30:43.397 --> 1:30:44.857
Jackie was always
the king of sabotage.

1:30:44.940 --> 1:30:48.443
MALCOLM: Regardless,
Sam was now stuck onstage

1:30:48.527 --> 1:30:52.239
with no sound
and a worked-up Boston crowd.

1:30:52.322 --> 1:30:53.866
Well, things
escalated quickly.

1:30:53.949 --> 1:30:56.076
My band was out of there
like some runaway slaves.

1:30:56.160 --> 1:30:57.703
Where the fuck y’all going?

1:30:57.786 --> 1:30:59.621
We’re musicians,
not bodyguards, baby.

1:30:59.705 --> 1:31:00.956
Good luck.

1:31:01.039 --> 1:31:03.792
But Sam, he just, he just
stood there on that stage.

1:31:03.876 --> 1:31:05.586
(booing continues)

1:31:06.628 --> 1:31:08.672
I remember thinking to myself,

1:31:08.755 --> 1:31:11.008
"This young brother is fittin’
to get himself killed."

1:31:11.091 --> 1:31:12.384
CASSIUS:
W-Well, then what happened?

1:31:13.510 --> 1:31:15.095
Something, uh...

1:31:16.638 --> 1:31:18.515
Something amazing happened.

1:31:18.599 --> 1:31:20.267
(booing continues)

1:31:22.060 --> 1:31:24.104
Y’all know "Chain Gang"?
All right,

1:31:24.188 --> 1:31:25.689
I’m-a, I’m-a do it
a cappella, all right?

1:31:25.772 --> 1:31:28.150
(speaking indistinctly)

1:31:28.233 --> 1:31:30.444
-MAN: I’ll kick your ass!
-(angry chatter)

1:31:30.527 --> 1:31:32.362
All right, let’s go.

1:31:32.446 --> 1:31:33.697
-All right.
-Let’s go.

1:31:35.449 --> 1:31:37.951
(grunting rhythmically)

1:31:42.164 --> 1:31:44.333
(booing quiets)

1:31:44.416 --> 1:31:45.500
Come on. (grunts)

1:31:49.129 --> 1:31:50.797
(Malcolm grunting rhythmically)

1:31:53.008 --> 1:31:54.760
-(booing stops)
-(audience stomping, grunting)

1:31:56.595 --> 1:32:00.057
-♪ All together, yeah ♪
-(grunting, stomping)

1:32:01.850 --> 1:32:03.894
♪ Everybody ♪

1:32:06.438 --> 1:32:07.564
(Cassius grunts)

1:32:07.648 --> 1:32:09.608
(rhythmic grunting
and stomping continue)

1:32:09.691 --> 1:32:11.109
Let me hear you.

1:32:12.945 --> 1:32:15.822
♪ You got it, you got it ♪

1:32:17.032 --> 1:32:20.369
♪ Sounds so good, yeah ♪

1:32:20.452 --> 1:32:22.746
♪ Ah, yeah ♪

1:32:22.829 --> 1:32:24.790
♪ That’s the sound of the men ♪

1:32:24.873 --> 1:32:27.084
♪ Working on the chain ♪

1:32:27.167 --> 1:32:29.962
♪ The gang ♪

1:32:30.045 --> 1:32:31.964
♪ That’s the sound of the men ♪

1:32:32.047 --> 1:32:35.300
♪ Working on the chain gang ♪

1:32:35.384 --> 1:32:37.427
♪ All day long
they’re singing... ♪

1:32:37.511 --> 1:32:39.054
MALCOLM:
Yeah, and I saw him up there,

1:32:39.137 --> 1:32:41.640
covered in sweat and...
and singing to ’em.

1:32:41.723 --> 1:32:43.392
But, you know,
in the back where I was,

1:32:43.475 --> 1:32:45.102
you couldn’t hear anything
except that chant.

1:32:45.185 --> 1:32:47.771
(grunting and stomping
drown out singing)

1:32:47.854 --> 1:32:50.315
You know, and...
you know what?

1:32:50.399 --> 1:32:54.444
That was, uh...
that was good enough.

1:32:55.737 --> 1:32:57.906
Yes, that was...

1:32:59.574 --> 1:33:01.618
...that was
one hell of a show, Sam.

1:33:01.702 --> 1:33:05.330
(stomping and grunting
continue)

1:33:05.414 --> 1:33:07.749
CASSIUS:
That sounds like something.

1:33:09.584 --> 1:33:11.044
It really was, Cash.

1:33:11.128 --> 1:33:13.505
It really was.

1:33:15.299 --> 1:33:19.344
Brother, you could
move mountains

1:33:19.428 --> 1:33:21.638
without lifting a finger.

1:33:24.057 --> 1:33:26.393
Listen, if-if I give you
a hard time, it’s...

1:33:26.476 --> 1:33:29.313
you know, it’s only because
I-I think so highly of you.

1:33:30.981 --> 1:33:32.816
You know, you brothers,
you-you all are-are

1:33:32.899 --> 1:33:34.276
our bright and shining future.

1:33:34.359 --> 1:33:37.904
I... I never, I never
lose sight of that.

1:33:37.988 --> 1:33:40.782
Well, you’re part of
that future, too, Malcolm.

1:33:40.866 --> 1:33:43.035
(Cassius chuckles)

1:33:44.369 --> 1:33:45.912
I’m flattered, really. I’m...

1:33:45.996 --> 1:33:48.665
Taking the world
on your shoulders is

1:33:48.749 --> 1:33:50.042
bad for your health.

1:33:50.125 --> 1:33:51.501
Yeah, well,

1:33:51.585 --> 1:33:54.421
he won’t have to carry it
by himself much longer.

1:33:54.504 --> 1:33:57.841
’Cause we gonna be
in the Nation together.

1:34:00.927 --> 1:34:02.346
Malcolm...

1:34:02.429 --> 1:34:04.056
I know.

1:34:05.557 --> 1:34:07.017
I know.

1:34:09.144 --> 1:34:10.395
What is it?

1:34:14.399 --> 1:34:16.151
Malcolm?

1:34:20.072 --> 1:34:22.407
Well, like I said, my, um...

1:34:22.491 --> 1:34:26.370
my relationship
with, uh, the Nation has...

1:34:26.453 --> 1:34:28.663
has gotten complicated.

1:34:30.165 --> 1:34:33.418
I-I don’t know how much longer
I’ll be in it.

1:34:34.961 --> 1:34:38.340
Wait a second. You’re leaving
the Nation of Islam?

1:34:40.092 --> 1:34:42.928
I thought once you went in,
you were in it for life.

1:34:43.011 --> 1:34:45.806
(chuckles):
I guess I’ll be, uh...

1:34:45.889 --> 1:34:48.308
I’ll be putting that theory
to the test, Sam.

1:34:48.392 --> 1:34:50.727
CASSIUS:
Why would you want to leave?

1:34:53.772 --> 1:34:55.482
All the things you told me.

1:34:56.691 --> 1:34:59.236
The things you showed me
that the Nation does.

1:34:59.319 --> 1:35:01.279
Oh, Cash, there’s...

1:35:01.363 --> 1:35:03.281
there’s lots of good and
righteous brothers and sisters

1:35:03.365 --> 1:35:06.284
in the Nation,
but it’s the leadership

1:35:06.368 --> 1:35:08.620
that has-has shown
that it’s not up to the task.

1:35:08.703 --> 1:35:10.539
Wait.

1:35:10.622 --> 1:35:15.043
So you’re gonna help me
cross over to being a Muslim

1:35:15.127 --> 1:35:17.129
and then quit being Muslim?

1:35:17.212 --> 1:35:19.089
No. No, no, no. No, Cassius.

1:35:19.172 --> 1:35:22.134
I will always,
always be Muslim.

1:35:22.217 --> 1:35:25.512
I-In, you know, in fact, I-I...

1:35:25.595 --> 1:35:31.059
I guess you could say, uh, I’m
becoming more Muslim than ever.

1:35:33.478 --> 1:35:34.855
I’m not understanding.

1:35:36.189 --> 1:35:37.732
Well, uh...

1:35:37.816 --> 1:35:40.610
I’m not leaving just to be
out alone in the world.

1:35:40.694 --> 1:35:42.612
I’m...

1:35:42.696 --> 1:35:44.865
I’m leaving to...

1:35:47.117 --> 1:35:49.035
I’m leaving to start
a new organization,

1:35:49.119 --> 1:35:53.123
one-one that adheres
more closely to the, uh, honest

1:35:53.206 --> 1:35:56.001
and, uh, righteous tenets
of Islam.

1:35:58.753 --> 1:36:02.382
Who’s gonna be
in this new organization?

1:36:02.466 --> 1:36:06.470
I think lots of people
will follow me over, Cash.

1:36:06.553 --> 1:36:08.346
Especially, uh...

1:36:10.098 --> 1:36:12.350
...i-if you-you come with me.

1:36:28.492 --> 1:36:29.784
Say something.

1:36:29.868 --> 1:36:31.453
-You motherfucker!
-Wait, wait, wait, wait.

1:36:31.536 --> 1:36:33.413
Hey, hey, Cash, Cash, Cash.
Hey!

1:36:33.497 --> 1:36:35.373
You’ve been using me!

1:36:35.457 --> 1:36:37.000
No, no, brother,
I’m trying to save you.

1:36:37.083 --> 1:36:39.169
-Wait. -You’re the only one
that needs saving!

1:36:39.252 --> 1:36:41.213
-No.
-MALCOLM: Cash.

1:36:41.296 --> 1:36:42.923
-(sighs)
-Cash.

1:36:44.090 --> 1:36:45.675
If you don’t believe
in your heart

1:36:45.759 --> 1:36:48.345
I’ve been
an honest friend to you,

1:36:48.428 --> 1:36:50.597
then-then you shouldn’t
join me, brother.

1:36:50.680 --> 1:36:52.807
If there’s any-any part of you
that-that believes

1:36:52.891 --> 1:36:55.393
that our time together
has been motivated in any way

1:36:55.477 --> 1:37:00.023
by selfishness
or-or opportunism on my part...

1:37:00.106 --> 1:37:02.692
brother, I...

1:37:02.776 --> 1:37:04.986
brother, I encourage you,

1:37:05.070 --> 1:37:06.905
walk away from me.

1:37:08.281 --> 1:37:10.575
Walk away from me with
a clear mind and conscience,

1:37:10.659 --> 1:37:12.494
knowing that that is
the right thing,

1:37:12.577 --> 1:37:14.788
that’s-that’s the only thing
you can do.

1:37:22.003 --> 1:37:25.090
MAN: Cassius Marcellus Clay,
you in there, champ?

1:37:25.173 --> 1:37:26.341
(knock on door)

1:37:26.424 --> 1:37:27.842
MAN 2:
Tell us about what happened...

1:37:27.926 --> 1:37:30.095
JAMAAL: We got a bunch
of reporters out here.

1:37:30.178 --> 1:37:32.931
(reporters chattering)

1:37:33.014 --> 1:37:35.100
There they are.

1:37:36.726 --> 1:37:41.815
Some... someone must have saw
me and Sam downstairs.

1:37:41.898 --> 1:37:45.694
Uh, well, you can’t blame them
for wanting a word

1:37:45.777 --> 1:37:48.238
from the new world champion.

1:37:48.321 --> 1:37:50.657
(Cassius clears throat, sighs)

1:37:50.740 --> 1:37:53.827
Yeah. (sniffs)

1:37:53.910 --> 1:37:55.912
I guess I got to go
talk to them,

1:37:55.996 --> 1:37:57.789
help them sell a few papers.

1:37:57.872 --> 1:37:59.708
MALCOLM:
Absolutely.

1:38:12.804 --> 1:38:14.973
(sighs)

1:38:15.807 --> 1:38:17.726
You coming?

1:38:26.109 --> 1:38:27.611
Um...

1:38:27.694 --> 1:38:29.112
Well, I...

1:38:29.195 --> 1:38:32.574
I don’t have any comments
to make right now, Cash. I...

1:38:32.657 --> 1:38:35.201
(chuckles) And besides, they’re
here to see you, brother.

1:38:35.285 --> 1:38:37.495
Not here to see me.

1:38:38.997 --> 1:38:41.333
I want you standing with me.

1:38:53.762 --> 1:38:55.430
Very well.

1:38:55.513 --> 1:38:57.307
Uh...

1:38:57.390 --> 1:38:59.601
You brothers will excuse us.

1:39:05.690 --> 1:39:07.192
(reporters clamoring)

1:39:07.275 --> 1:39:09.569
CASSIUS: I told you suckers
I was the greatest!

1:39:09.653 --> 1:39:11.154
All of you must bow!

1:39:11.237 --> 1:39:12.822
Oh, I think you guys...

1:39:12.906 --> 1:39:16.242
This is one strange
fucking night.

1:39:18.161 --> 1:39:19.579
Yeah.

1:39:21.206 --> 1:39:23.708
Hey, you know I know what’s
going on out there, right?

1:39:23.792 --> 1:39:25.251
Uh, yeah.

1:39:25.335 --> 1:39:27.504
You know, Cassius, he out there
talking to the press.

1:39:27.587 --> 1:39:29.089
No, I mean out...

1:39:29.172 --> 1:39:31.007
out-out there.

1:39:32.467 --> 1:39:34.469
I mean...

1:39:34.552 --> 1:39:37.180
just ’cause I haven’t released
any records about the movement

1:39:37.263 --> 1:39:40.475
don’t mean I haven’t written
any songs about the movement.

1:39:40.558 --> 1:39:42.268
Come on, man.
Look, you know Malcolm.

1:39:42.352 --> 1:39:44.979
He’s all fire and brimstone
about everything, man.

1:39:45.063 --> 1:39:47.649
But when I heard the
Bob Dylan song, I was mad, man.

1:39:47.732 --> 1:39:49.484
Why?

1:39:50.652 --> 1:39:52.862
’Cause it’s fucking good.

1:39:52.946 --> 1:39:54.614
Well, good.
(chuckles)

1:39:54.698 --> 1:39:55.699
Good.

1:39:55.782 --> 1:39:57.409
You should feel
competitive, man.

1:39:57.492 --> 1:40:00.078
It’s not just ’cause
it was good. It’s...

1:40:00.161 --> 1:40:01.788
I felt like...

1:40:03.289 --> 1:40:05.792
...felt like I should’ve
written that song.

1:40:07.419 --> 1:40:10.630
I mean, I’m-I’m calling myself
"Mr. Soul," and I...

1:40:10.714 --> 1:40:13.216
I haven’t written anything
like that.

1:40:16.010 --> 1:40:18.596
Why don’t you start?

1:40:18.680 --> 1:40:20.306
I started working on something.

1:40:20.390 --> 1:40:22.225
Um...

1:40:22.308 --> 1:40:25.562
started working on something
the first day I heard the song.

1:40:26.730 --> 1:40:27.939
Really?

1:40:28.022 --> 1:40:30.984
Yeah, but it’s-it’s...
it’s different.

1:40:31.067 --> 1:40:34.529
And I haven’t even played it
for a crowd yet.

1:40:37.991 --> 1:40:40.285
How does it go?

1:40:41.828 --> 1:40:44.372
All these so-called experts
were all wrong.

1:40:44.456 --> 1:40:47.041
Next time, don’t-don’t ask
no bookies who’s gonna win.

1:40:47.125 --> 1:40:49.544
You come to me.
I’ll tell you who’s gonna win.

1:40:49.627 --> 1:40:51.546
Cassius, uh,
is it fair to assume

1:40:51.629 --> 1:40:53.339
that, since Malcolm X
is standing here with you,

1:40:53.423 --> 1:40:55.884
that you’re seriously
considering becoming a Muslim?

1:40:55.967 --> 1:40:58.762
I’m not considering anything.
I am a Muslim.

1:40:58.845 --> 1:41:01.014
And from this day forward,
I no longer want to be called

1:41:01.097 --> 1:41:03.224
-by the name Cassius Clay.
-REPORTERS: Mm.

1:41:03.308 --> 1:41:04.559
That is a slave name.

1:41:04.642 --> 1:41:05.977
What are we supposed
to call you, then?

1:41:06.060 --> 1:41:08.813
You will refer to me
as Cassius X.

1:41:08.897 --> 1:41:09.898
-(laughter)
-REPORTER: Malcolm,

1:41:09.981 --> 1:41:11.316
have you been giving Clay
advice

1:41:11.399 --> 1:41:12.776
-on his religious beliefs?
-Look at that.

1:41:12.859 --> 1:41:14.611
MALCOLM:
Well, he’s my brother and...

1:41:14.694 --> 1:41:16.321
New heavyweight champion
of the world.

1:41:16.404 --> 1:41:17.989
MALCOLM:
...my friend.

1:41:18.072 --> 1:41:21.159
I express what I know
and understand, but...

1:41:21.242 --> 1:41:23.244
Cassius,
he has a mind of his own,

1:41:23.328 --> 1:41:25.413
-an understanding of his own.
-Mm-hmm.

1:41:25.497 --> 1:41:26.790
REPORTER 2:
Uh, Cassius, are you gonna

1:41:26.873 --> 1:41:28.082
-give Sonny Liston a rematch?
-Cassius.

1:41:28.166 --> 1:41:30.251
-Cassius. -Cassius.
-Oh, no, man. Come on.

1:41:30.335 --> 1:41:32.128
-Sonny Liston a rematch?
-(chuckles)

1:41:32.212 --> 1:41:34.464
He’s still in the hospital
from after tonight.

1:41:34.547 --> 1:41:35.965
-(laughter, applause)
-Say, man,

1:41:36.049 --> 1:41:37.509
now that this is out the way,

1:41:37.592 --> 1:41:40.178
don’t you think
it’s about time to party?

1:41:40.261 --> 1:41:42.138
-I’d say so.
-Yeah, definitely.

1:41:42.222 --> 1:41:43.223
(cheering)

1:41:43.306 --> 1:41:44.641
CASSIUS:
Man, I’m so fast!

1:41:44.724 --> 1:41:46.434
I’m so fast, after the fight,

1:41:46.518 --> 1:41:48.812
-Miami Vice tried to give me
a speeding ticket! -(cheering)

1:41:48.895 --> 1:41:52.106
If you take Sonny Liston,
Joe Louis

1:41:52.190 --> 1:41:54.651
-and Rocky Marciano...
-(clapping, encouraging chatter)

1:41:54.734 --> 1:41:56.778
I’ll whup ’em all
the same night!

1:41:56.861 --> 1:41:58.530
(cheering)

1:41:58.613 --> 1:42:00.490
That’s what I’ll do next time!

1:42:00.573 --> 1:42:02.283
You know I’m the greatest.

1:42:02.367 --> 1:42:04.494
-OTHERS: Yeah!
-Who’s the greatest?

1:42:04.577 --> 1:42:05.787
-OTHERS: You are!
-That’s right.

1:42:05.870 --> 1:42:07.413
Malcolm, come on.
Put that thing down.

1:42:07.497 --> 1:42:09.332
Come over here.
Someone get a picture of us.

1:42:09.415 --> 1:42:10.625
-(assenting, applause)
-Come on.

1:42:10.708 --> 1:42:12.418
I want a picture with Malcolm.
Come on.

1:42:12.502 --> 1:42:14.337
Let’s see, man.

1:42:14.420 --> 1:42:16.381
You know it’s right.
That’s what I’m talking about.

1:42:16.464 --> 1:42:17.507
Give me some, brothers.

1:42:17.590 --> 1:42:19.425
That’s it. My brother.

1:42:19.509 --> 1:42:20.927
My main man.

1:42:21.010 --> 1:42:22.095
And you, too.

1:42:22.178 --> 1:42:24.305
I told ’em! I told ’em.

1:42:24.389 --> 1:42:26.266
I proved it. I was in Rome.

1:42:26.349 --> 1:42:27.851
They said they had
a man who could beat me.

1:42:27.934 --> 1:42:29.435
-MAN: Yeah!
-Malcolm, come on.

1:42:29.519 --> 1:42:30.687
Get over here.

1:42:30.770 --> 1:42:32.355
-I whupped him, too.
-(cheering, applause)

